WEBVTT

00:02.173 --> 00:03.834
Meredith:
OVER THE PAST 20 YEARS,

00:03.834 --> 00:06.547
ONE OF THE MOST VALUABLE TOOLS
A DOCTOR HAS IS THE ALGORITHM.

00:06.547 --> 00:09.800
YOUR PATIENT'S MAIN COMPLAINT
GOES INTO A BOX...

00:09.800 --> 00:11.722
CRISTINA WAS SUPPOSED TO
FLY OUT WITH US THIS MORNING,

00:11.722 --> 00:13.344
AND SHE DIDN'T SHOW.

00:13.344 --> 00:15.306
...AND THEN THE FORMULA HELPS
YOU DECIDE WHAT TO DO NEXT.

00:15.306 --> 00:17.138
[ SIGHS ]
HER PHONE'S STILL OFF.

00:17.138 --> 00:20.731
NO, UH, DEREK, ALL -- ALL SHE
SAID WAS, "THAT'S HOW IT GOES."

00:20.731 --> 00:22.403
LAST NIGHT
AFTER THE CEREMONY.

00:22.403 --> 00:24.105
AND THEN
THAT SMUG IDIOT'S SPEECH

00:24.105 --> 00:26.026
WAS A 20-MINUTE ODE
TO HIMSELF.

00:26.026 --> 00:28.069
MA'AM,
WE'RE SHUTTING THE DOORS.

00:28.069 --> 00:29.450
SHE'LL JUST BE
ONE SECOND.

00:29.450 --> 00:32.203
[ DING ]
HIS RESEARCH
WASN'T EVEN RESEARCH.

00:32.203 --> 00:35.116
I READ HIS PAPER ON LYMPH NODES.
IT SOUNDED PLAGIARIZED.

00:35.116 --> 00:37.368
I'M VERY SORRY, BUT YOU'LL NEED
TO PUT YOUR PHONE AWAY.

00:37.368 --> 00:38.709
I HEARD YOU.

00:38.709 --> 00:40.751
UH, I'LL CALL YOU
WHEN WE LAND.

00:40.751 --> 00:43.664
BUT WHAT HAPPENS WHEN THE
PROBLEM DOESN'T FIT INTO A BOX?

00:43.664 --> 00:44.665
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

00:44.665 --> 00:46.217
ALL RIGHT,
MAMA HUNG UP ON US.

00:46.217 --> 00:48.379
ZOLA, TIME TO PUT ON
YOUR SHOES, SWEETIE.

00:48.379 --> 00:50.171
WELL...
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

00:50.171 --> 00:52.553
...YOU'RE SUDDENLY ON YOUR OWN,
UNEXPECTEDLY,

00:52.553 --> 00:55.436
WITH ABOUT A THOUSAND PATHS
TO CHOOSE FROM.

00:55.436 --> 00:57.558
I SHOULD HAVE CALLED.
I KNOW.

00:57.558 --> 00:59.560
UH --
BUT IF I CALLED,
YOU'D HAVE SAID NO.

00:59.560 --> 01:03.274
AND THEN I WOULDN'T GET TO SEE
HOW GROWN UP YOU ARE.

01:03.274 --> 01:05.276
ZOLA! WOW!

01:05.276 --> 01:08.319
LOOK AT YOU!
WHAT ARE YOU, LIKE 16 NOW?

01:08.319 --> 01:11.282
AND I WANTED TO MEET
MY NEPHEW. OH.

01:11.282 --> 01:13.033
UM...
HELLO TO YOU, TOO.

01:13.033 --> 01:14.615
I HAVEN'T TALKED TO YOU
IN LIKE TWO MONTHS.

01:14.615 --> 01:16.157
AMY,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

01:16.157 --> 01:18.459
A...THING HAPPENED.

01:20.251 --> 01:21.792
JAMES PROPOSED.

01:21.792 --> 01:23.334
AH!
CONGRATULATIONS.

01:23.334 --> 01:25.256
AND I FREAKED.
I'M SURE YOU DID.

01:25.256 --> 01:27.668
JUST SORT OF FREAKED, NOT -- NOT
FLEE-THE-COUNTRY FREAKED.

01:27.668 --> 01:30.171
JUST...SUDDENLY...
[ SIGHS ]

01:30.171 --> 01:31.472
THERE'S THE POSSIBILITY

01:31.472 --> 01:33.424
THAT I MAY BE FACING
A DIFFERENT KIND OF LIFE --

01:33.424 --> 01:35.176
THE KIND THAT
YOU AND MEREDITH HAVE --

01:35.176 --> 01:36.847
SO I THOUGHT
I WOULD COME VISIT

01:36.847 --> 01:39.980
AND SEE WHAT IT'S LIKE
AND GET...UNFREAKED.

01:39.980 --> 01:40.981
HOPEFULLY.

01:40.981 --> 01:42.643
YOU'RE MAD.

01:42.643 --> 01:44.225
NO. I'M HAPPY
TO SHOW YOU.

01:44.225 --> 01:47.398
HEY, ZOLA, AUNTIE AMY IS GONNA
PLAY WITH YOU AND BAILEY TODAY

01:47.398 --> 01:49.190
WHILE I GO TO WORK.
OH. OH.

01:49.190 --> 01:51.282
WOW. REALLY NOT MAD.
NO, I'M EXCITED.

01:51.282 --> 01:53.234
YEAH.
[ CHUCKLES ]
SO, BAILEY GETS A BOTTLE
IN AN HOUR.

01:53.234 --> 01:55.286
HIS SCHEDULE'S
ON THE REFRIGERATOR.

01:55.286 --> 01:57.198
ZOLA LIKES
TO STICK STUFF UP HER NOSE,

01:57.198 --> 01:58.239
SO KEEP AN EYE ON HER.

01:58.239 --> 01:59.410
OH. OKAY.

01:59.410 --> 02:01.542
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

02:01.542 --> 02:03.043
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

02:05.706 --> 02:07.918
Callie: OKAY,
SO, WE TURKEY-BASTE ME IN MAY.

02:07.918 --> 02:10.251
AND THEN THE BABY'S BORN
IN FEBRUARY?
YEP.

02:12.253 --> 02:14.134
SORRY. JUST, UH, NEED TO BORROW
SOME TOOTHPASTE.

02:14.134 --> 02:15.306
AS YOU WERE.

02:16.597 --> 02:18.889
OKAY, SO, I TAKE OFF THE SPRING,
RECOVER, NURSE,

02:18.889 --> 02:20.261
AND THEN YOU TAKE OFF
THE SUMMER.

02:20.261 --> 02:22.142
MM-HMM. AND THEN I PUT KAREV
IN CHARGE OF PEDS.

02:22.142 --> 02:23.764
I THINK THAT
THAT WORKS.

02:23.764 --> 02:25.105
ARE YOU SURE ABOUT THAT?

02:25.105 --> 02:26.267
'CAUSE IF YOU'RE GONE
IN THE SUMMER,

02:26.267 --> 02:27.818
YOU'RE GONE
WHEN THE NEW INTERNS START.

02:27.818 --> 02:29.530
YOU REALLY WANT KAREV
IN CHARGE OF ALL THE NEW KIDS?

02:29.530 --> 02:32.193
MAYBE -- MAYBE PUSH OFF
THE INSEMINATION TO JULY?
KEPNER. KEPNER.

02:33.274 --> 02:34.445
GET OUT OF MY VAGINA.

02:35.536 --> 02:37.037
YES. RIGHT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:37.037 --> 02:39.159
[ Sighing ]
OH, WOW.

02:39.159 --> 02:41.161
IT'S REALLY ONLY BEEN
TWO NIGHTS?

02:41.161 --> 02:43.163
'CAUSE IT FEELS LIKE 10.

02:43.163 --> 02:44.625
[ DOG BARKING ]

02:44.625 --> 02:46.457
NO. I'M NOT GONNA HAVE TIME
TO PRE-ROUND.

02:46.457 --> 02:47.878
SCREW PRE-ROUNDS.

02:47.878 --> 02:49.250
YOUR PEDS FELLOW
NEEDS A CONSULT.

02:49.250 --> 02:50.751
[ LAUGHS ]

02:54.635 --> 02:56.757
NO! NO, NO, NO. WAIT -- WAIT.
YOU HAVE TO WORK, TOO.

02:56.757 --> 02:58.178
YOU'RE AVOIDING
SOMETHING.

02:58.178 --> 02:59.220
LESS TALK, MORE STUFF.

02:59.220 --> 03:01.352
[ SIGHS ] NO, ALEX.
I'M SERIOUS.

03:01.352 --> 03:03.974
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT'S GOING ON?

03:03.974 --> 03:06.727
I GOT AN OFFER FROM LeBACKES
TO WORK AT HIS PRACTICE.

03:06.727 --> 03:08.569
IT'S A GOOD OFFER --
A REALLY GOOD OFFER.

03:08.569 --> 03:10.361
OH! THAT'S GREAT!

03:11.522 --> 03:13.113
WHY DON'T YOU LOOK LIKE
IT'S GREAT?

03:13.113 --> 03:15.236
I'M SUPPOSED TO GIVE THEM
AN ANSWER BY THE END OF THE DAY.

03:15.236 --> 03:16.947
OH.
[ SIGHS ]

03:16.947 --> 03:19.159
ROBBINS IS GONNA BE SO PISSED.
WHAT AM I GONNA TELL HER?

03:19.159 --> 03:23.914
JUST BE PLEASANT
AND CONFIDENT AND FIRM,

03:23.914 --> 03:25.586
SMILE [LAUGHS]
WHEN YOU TALK,

03:25.586 --> 03:27.668
AND JUST TELL HER
HOW EXCITED YOU ARE

03:27.668 --> 03:29.630
ABOUT THIS GREAT
NEW OPPORTUNITY.

03:29.630 --> 03:31.752
IF SHE STARTS MAKING
HER SCARY, ANGRY FACE,

03:31.752 --> 03:33.334
DISTRACT HER
WITH A COMPLIMENT.

03:35.215 --> 03:37.298
THAT WORKS?
THE COMPLIMENTS THING?

03:37.298 --> 03:38.929
MM-HMM.

03:38.929 --> 03:40.180
GOD, YOU'RE SEXY.

03:40.180 --> 03:42.603
DOESN'T WORK ON ME.

03:44.184 --> 03:46.186
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:47.608 --> 03:50.691
Shane:
FRANKIE McNEIL, POST-OP DAY 2
AFTER LVAD IMPLANTATION.

03:50.691 --> 03:52.943
CURRENTLY LISTED STATUS 1A
FOR TRANSPLANT.

03:52.943 --> 03:54.405
DESPITE THE LVAD,

03:54.405 --> 03:56.447
WE HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE TO
REVERSE HER END-ORGAN DAMAGE.

03:56.447 --> 03:59.159
THE GOOD NEWS IS, A HEART
BECAME AVAILABLE THIS MORNING.

03:59.159 --> 04:01.782
WE'RE JUST WAITING
FOR CONFIRMATION FROM
THE HOSPITAL IN OAKLAND.

04:01.782 --> 04:04.164
I'M SORRY,
BUT WHO ARE YOU AGAIN?
Arizona:
OH, I'M SORRY.

04:04.164 --> 04:06.417
UM, DR. RUSSELL IS OUR HEAD
OF CARDIOTHORACIC SURGERY.

04:06.417 --> 04:07.748
SINCE DR. YANG'S
NOT BACK,

04:07.748 --> 04:10.130
HE'LL BE PERFORMING
FRANKIE'S TRANSPLANT TODAY.

04:10.130 --> 04:11.422
BUT DR. YANG'S
OUR SURGEON.

04:11.422 --> 04:14.295
NO OFFENSE, BUT HOW DO WE KNOW
YOU'RE AS GOOD?

04:14.295 --> 04:16.006
I'M AN ATTENDING.
SHE'S A FELLOW.

04:16.006 --> 04:18.008
TRUST ME --
I'M AS GOOD.

04:18.008 --> 04:20.220
Alex: DR. ROBBINS AND I WILL BE
IN THE O.R. THE ENTIRE TIME.

04:20.220 --> 04:21.221
FRANKIE'S IN GOOD HANDS.

04:21.221 --> 04:22.843
AND LINK?

04:22.843 --> 04:24.264
Leah:
BREATH SOUNDS ARE STRONG,

04:24.264 --> 04:25.726
AND THIS MORNING'S ECHO
WAS ALL CLEAR,

04:25.726 --> 04:27.728
AND HIS HEART PUMP IS DOING
EVERYTHING IT SHOULD.

04:27.728 --> 04:30.190
Link, buddy, that's great.
You're getting better.

04:30.190 --> 04:31.942
WHEN CAN IVY
COME BACK IN HERE?

04:31.942 --> 04:33.734
UM...

04:33.734 --> 04:35.356
WELL, SHE'S STILL SICK,

04:35.356 --> 04:37.277
SO SHE NEEDS TO STAY IN THERE
A LITTLE BIT LONGER.

04:39.239 --> 04:41.322
UNFORTUNATELY,
IVY'S STILL IN REJECTION.

04:41.322 --> 04:43.243
UNOS HAS HER LISTED
AS STATUS 1B,

04:43.243 --> 04:46.166
AND WE'RE MONITORING HER
VERY CLOSELY.

04:48.208 --> 04:50.331
[ SIGHS ]

04:50.331 --> 04:52.292
PAGE, WHEN WE KNOW
THE HEART'S A GO...

04:52.292 --> 04:54.174
Woman:
HERE YOU GO, DOCTOR.

04:54.174 --> 04:56.086
SO...DR. YANG
WON'T BE BACK TODAY?

04:56.086 --> 04:58.298
WELL, I HAVEN'T HEARD FROM
HER, AND I CAN'T EXACTLY
POSTPONE THE SURGERY.

04:58.298 --> 04:59.299
HAS ANYONE HEARD FROM HER?

05:01.261 --> 05:03.223
Y-- JUST MAKE SURE THAT
FRANKIE'S READY AND PREPPED.

05:05.386 --> 05:07.267
WHY ARE YOU HOVERING?

05:09.189 --> 05:11.021
Woman: THANK YOU.
WHAT'S WRONG
WITH YOUR FACE?

05:11.021 --> 05:13.273
I LIKE YOUR HAIR.
OH, WHAT DID YOU DO?

05:14.234 --> 05:15.526
RADIOLOGY'S BACKED UP.

05:15.526 --> 05:17.398
CAN YOU GET ME IN LINE
FOR THE NEXT AVAILABLE MRI?

05:17.398 --> 05:18.899
SURE.
HEY, SHEPHERD,

05:18.899 --> 05:21.201
YOU'RE BACK TO MORE OF A REGULAR
SURGICAL SCHEDULE, RIGHT?

05:21.201 --> 05:22.533
YES. WHY?

05:22.533 --> 05:24.114
THE FOUNDATION ASKED ME
TO REPORT ON THE STATUS

05:24.114 --> 05:25.536
OF OUR SURGEON-RUN
RESEARCH PROJECTS --

05:25.536 --> 05:27.658
WANT TO SEE WHICH ONES
ARE ACTUALLY GETTING RESULTS.

05:27.658 --> 05:29.329
SO, WHAT, THEY CAN START
SHUTTING OTHER ONES DOWN?

05:29.329 --> 05:31.331
NEUROLOGICAL RESEARCH
TAKES A REALLY LONG TIME.

05:31.331 --> 05:33.163
I'M LOOKING AT ALL THE PROJECTS,
DEREK, NOT JUST YOURS.

05:33.163 --> 05:35.125
WE CAN START MAKING
THESE DECISIONS OURSELVES

05:35.125 --> 05:37.337
OR WAIT FOR THE FOUNDATION
TO DO IT FOR US.

05:37.337 --> 05:38.549
REMEMBER --
DR. TORRES AND I

05:38.549 --> 05:40.801
HAVE A PRESIDENTIAL
SEAL OF APPROVAL.

05:42.302 --> 05:44.304
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

05:45.766 --> 05:47.057
YOU'RE BACK!

05:47.057 --> 05:48.969
YOU'RE GONNA WANT
TO STAY AWAY FROM ME TODAY.

05:48.969 --> 05:50.851
WHERE'S CRISTINA?
SHE MUST BE DEVASTATED.

05:50.851 --> 05:53.313
IF I WERE HERE, I'D BE
FACE-FIRST IN A PILE OF
CHOCOLATE-CHIP COOKIES.

05:53.313 --> 05:54.435
STOP IT!

05:54.435 --> 05:55.976
CRISTINA YANG
DOESN'T NEED YOUR PITY!

05:55.976 --> 05:57.938
SHE WAS ROBBED!
AND YOU ROBBED HER!

05:57.938 --> 05:59.319
OH! I DID?

05:59.319 --> 06:01.361
YES! YOU! YOU'RE AN AVERY
BY ASSOCIATION!

06:01.361 --> 06:04.114
THAT PACK OF FOOLS CAN'T TELL
THEIR ASSES FROM THEIR ELBOWS,

06:04.114 --> 06:05.866
NEVER MIND
AN AWARD-WINNING SURGEON

06:05.866 --> 06:07.367
VERSUS SOME HALF-WIT

06:07.367 --> 06:09.490
WHO TINKERS WITH SCIENCE KITS
IN HIS MOTHER'S BASEMENT!

06:10.831 --> 06:12.623
I TOLD YOU TO STAY AWAY FROM ME
TODAY, DIDN'T I?

06:12.623 --> 06:13.834
MM-HMM.

06:13.834 --> 06:15.586
WHEN DID ALL THIS HAPPEN?
ABOUT A MONTH AGO.

06:15.586 --> 06:17.047
LeBACKES APPROACHED ME.

06:17.047 --> 06:19.550
I'VE BEEN DOING WORK WITH HIM
ON MY OFF TIME.

06:19.550 --> 06:21.592
HE THINKS I COULD MAKE
A REALLY GOOD FIT.

06:21.592 --> 06:24.004
SO YOU'VE ALREADY DECIDED?
YOU'RE LEAVING?

06:24.004 --> 06:25.265
NO.
I-I DON'T KNOW.

06:25.265 --> 06:27.177
I MEAN, MY FELLOWSHIP
IS ALMOST OVER, SO...

06:27.177 --> 06:29.219
WELL, UM,
WHEN DO THEY NEED TO KNOW BY?

06:29.219 --> 06:31.011
TONIGHT.

06:31.011 --> 06:32.813
[ SIGHS ]

06:32.813 --> 06:34.605
WHAT, YOU'RE NOT GONNA
YELL AT ME OR SOMETHING?

06:34.605 --> 06:35.816
[ PAGERS BEEP ]

06:35.816 --> 06:37.818
FRANKIE'S HEART
IS ON ITS WAY.

06:37.818 --> 06:40.571
[ Voice breaking ] SEE,
WE -- WE JUST DON'T UNDERSTAND.

06:40.571 --> 06:42.152
TWO DAYS AGO,
HE WAS FINE,

06:42.152 --> 06:44.234
AND NOW HE'S STRUGGLING
TO EVEN BREATHE.

06:44.234 --> 06:45.656
YOU GAVE HIM CHEMO
LAST NIGHT.

06:45.656 --> 06:47.237
IS THAT WHAT'S MAKING HIM
SO MUCH SICKER?

06:47.237 --> 06:49.409
I MEAN, I KNOW IT HAS SOMETHING
TO DO WITH THE GENE THERAPY.

06:49.409 --> 06:51.201
WELL, THE CHEMO OBLITERATED
THE BONE MARROW,

06:51.201 --> 06:53.203
WHICH CONTAINED
THE ENZYME-DEFICIENT CELLS.

06:53.203 --> 06:55.125
SUCH A MILD DOSE
WOULDN'T MAKE HIM SICK.

06:55.125 --> 06:57.337
WE BELIEVE HE PICKED UP
A VIRAL INFECTION.

06:57.337 --> 06:59.209
HOW?!
HE'S IN ISOLATION!

06:59.209 --> 07:01.211
HE -- HE HAS NO CONTACT
WITH ANYONE.

07:01.211 --> 07:02.543
HOW IS THAT POSSIBLE?

07:02.543 --> 07:04.344
YOUR SON HAS
NO IMMUNE SYSTEM.

07:04.344 --> 07:07.047
WE-WE'VE TAKEN EVERY PRECAUTION,
BUT THIS IS A HOSPITAL.

07:07.047 --> 07:09.179
LOOK AT HIM!
HE'S BARELY ALIVE!

07:09.179 --> 07:10.971
MAYBE WE SHOULD
JUST STOP EVERYTHING...

07:10.971 --> 07:12.893
YES.
...AND LET HIM GET BETTER,
JUST LET HIM REST.

07:12.893 --> 07:14.434
REMEMBER,
WE WENT THROUGH THIS.

07:14.434 --> 07:16.647
HE COULD GET SICKER
BEFORE HE GOT BETTER.

07:16.647 --> 07:19.109
WE'RE STILL ON TRACK
FOR THIS AFTERNOON.

07:19.109 --> 07:21.982
WHEN YOU INJECT AN HIV VIRUS
INTO OUR VERY-SICK LITTLE BOY.

07:21.982 --> 07:24.234
INJECT
A DEACTIVATED HIV --

07:24.234 --> 07:25.656
O-O-OKAY, LOOK, LOOK,

07:25.656 --> 07:29.069
W-WE JUST NEED TO HANG ON
A LITTLE WHILE LONGER.

07:29.069 --> 07:31.071
[ SIGHS ]
WE'RE ALMOST THERE.

07:31.071 --> 07:33.073
BRADEN.
[ WHIMPERS ]

07:35.335 --> 07:39.129
LET'S GIVE THIS KID
A NEW HEART, SHALL WE?

07:39.129 --> 07:40.631
10 BLADE.

07:41.632 --> 07:43.423
I'VE GOT IT,
DR. RUSSELL.

07:43.423 --> 07:45.085
YANG!

07:45.085 --> 07:48.138
THIS IS A SURPRISE.
WHEN'D YOU GET BACK?

07:48.138 --> 07:49.970
THANK YOU FOR COVERING, RUSSELL,
BUT I'VE GOT IT FROM HERE.

07:49.970 --> 07:51.301
I'M ALREADY SCRUBBED
AND READY TO GO.

07:51.301 --> 07:52.763
WHY DON'T YOU TAKE A LOAD OFF?
YOU MUST BE TIRED.

07:52.763 --> 07:55.355
I'VE FOLLOWED FRANKIE McNEIL
SINCE DAY 1. THANK YOU.

07:57.187 --> 07:59.439
TOUGH LOSS LAST NIGHT,
YANG.

07:59.439 --> 08:01.191
MUST HAVE STUNG.

08:01.191 --> 08:03.984
BETTER LUCK NEXT TIME.

08:07.317 --> 08:09.319
IT WAS AN HONOR
JUST TO BE NOMINATED.

08:11.912 --> 08:13.914
10 BLADE.

08:40.400 --> 08:43.233
WHAT ON EARTH
ARE YOU DOING HERE?!

08:43.233 --> 08:44.234
OHH!

08:44.234 --> 08:45.275
Both: MWAH!

08:45.275 --> 08:46.316
I LIKE
TO KEEP YOU GUESSING.

08:46.316 --> 08:47.317
OOH!

08:47.317 --> 08:48.649
YOU BETTER GET IN HERE

08:48.649 --> 08:51.071
BEFORE I DO SOMETHING
THAT WILL EMBARRASS HENRY.

08:51.071 --> 08:53.323
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

08:53.323 --> 08:55.656
OH, WOW!

08:55.656 --> 08:57.788
OOH! MMM.

08:57.788 --> 08:59.289
MM.

08:59.289 --> 09:01.331
MM. I SHOULD SURPRISE YOU
MORE OFTEN.

09:01.331 --> 09:02.793
[ LAUGHS ]

09:02.793 --> 09:04.374
WELL,
I'M NOT THAT SURPRISED.

09:04.374 --> 09:05.586
HOW COME?

09:05.586 --> 09:08.378
I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT SHOW UP
AND POKE AROUND,

09:08.378 --> 09:11.551
TRYING TO FIGURE OUT WHY
DR. YANG DIDN'T GET HER AWARD.

09:11.551 --> 09:13.724
OH, PLEASE. I PLANNED THIS TRIP
A LONG TIME AGO.

09:13.724 --> 09:15.806
I FIGURED YOU'D BE EXHAUSTED
FROM THE CEREMONY

09:15.806 --> 09:17.437
AND NEED
A LITTLE GETAWAY.

09:17.437 --> 09:19.139
YOU DIDN'T PLAN IT
AS A VICTORY LAP

09:19.139 --> 09:21.101
TO CELEBRATE
YANG'S BIG WIN?

09:21.101 --> 09:22.813
MM...THAT WOULD HAVE BEEN
A NICE FEATURE.

09:22.813 --> 09:24.524
MM. YEAH.

09:24.524 --> 09:27.527
BUT I THINK THE WEEKEND
WILL HAVE OTHER NICE FEATURES.

09:27.527 --> 09:29.319
OH. REALLY?

09:29.319 --> 09:30.821
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:30.821 --> 09:32.823
SO, WHY DON'T YOU FINISH
WHAT YOU'RE DOING?
MM-HMM.

09:32.823 --> 09:34.284
I'LL SIT HERE
AND WATCH THE MAGIC,

09:34.284 --> 09:36.406
AND THEN
I'LL TAKE YOU TO DINNER.

09:36.406 --> 09:37.658
MM.

09:37.658 --> 09:40.080
YES, DR. WEBBER.

09:40.080 --> 09:42.082
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

09:45.796 --> 09:46.797
HEY.

09:46.797 --> 09:49.049
HI. HOW ARE YOU?

09:49.049 --> 09:50.380
GOOD.

09:50.380 --> 09:51.802
HOW'D YOU SLEEP?

09:52.713 --> 09:53.804
FINE, THANKS.

09:53.804 --> 09:56.386
HAVE YOU TALKED TO CRISTINA?
IS SHE OKAY?

09:56.386 --> 09:57.768
I REALLY THOUGHT
THAT SHE HAD --

09:57.768 --> 09:59.519
YEAH, I-I KNOW.
I WAS SHOCKED, TOO.

09:59.519 --> 10:02.522
UM, SO...I NEED
TO COME HOME TONIGHT.

10:03.724 --> 10:05.395
YOU WANT TO TALK?

10:05.395 --> 10:06.857
I...

10:06.857 --> 10:08.398
I NEED MY iPOD.

10:08.398 --> 10:10.400
I WENT RUNNING TODAY,
AND I WISHED --
SURE. SURE.

10:11.902 --> 10:13.283
ARE YOU OKAY?

10:13.283 --> 10:14.364
YOU LOOK --

10:14.364 --> 10:16.196
STRESSED.
I'M A LITTLE STRESSED.

10:16.196 --> 10:18.238
I GOT TO COMPILE A REPORT
FOR THE FOUNDATION

10:18.238 --> 10:20.330
ON THE VALUE
OF PEOPLE'S RESEARCH PROJECTS,
[ DOOR OPENS ]

10:20.330 --> 10:23.243
'CAUSE WE'RE NOT GONNA
BE ABLE TO KEEP ALL OF
THEM, I DON'T THINK.

10:24.915 --> 10:25.916
WOW.

10:25.916 --> 10:27.668
WHAT?

10:27.668 --> 10:30.090
YOU GUYS DENY HER THE AWARD
AND NOT 24 HOURS LATER,

10:30.090 --> 10:31.712
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT
SHUTTING DOWN HER RESEARCH?

10:31.712 --> 10:33.714
YOU KNOW THAT THAT WAS, LIKE,
HER LIFE'S DREAM, RIGHT?

10:33.714 --> 10:36.056
[ PAGER BEEPS ]
THAT'S NOT WHAT WE'RE DOING.
THEY'RE LOOKING FOR WAYS TO --

10:36.056 --> 10:37.928
[ SIGHS ]
CLASSY MOVE, AVERY FAMILY.

10:37.928 --> 10:40.260
WAY TO MAKE IT
ALL ABOUT THE MEDICINE.

10:42.312 --> 10:44.394
April:
OKAY. WHAT DO WE GOT?

10:44.394 --> 10:45.726
SAM ROANE, 23 --

10:45.726 --> 10:47.357
BEEN WALKING CROSS-COUNTRY
FOR THE PAST THREE MONTHS,

10:47.357 --> 10:48.608
STOPPING ONLY FOR SLEEP

10:48.608 --> 10:50.070
AND THE PICKUP
THAT TOOK HIM OUT.

10:50.070 --> 10:52.272
HYPOTENSIVE
WITH MULTIPLE BLUNT TRAUMA

10:52.272 --> 10:54.695
AND DEFORMITY
TO THE RIGHT LOWER EXTREMITY.

10:54.695 --> 10:56.366
PARAMEDICS SPLINTED HIM
IN THE FIELD.

10:56.366 --> 10:58.448
SO, THREE MONTHS? THAT MEANS
YOU STARTED WALKING FROM...

10:58.448 --> 10:59.990
WILMINGTON.
Callie: WOW.

10:59.990 --> 11:01.541
WERE YOU, UH, WALKING
FOR CHARITY?

11:01.541 --> 11:03.543
NO. I MEAN, I FELL IN WITH A FEW
CANCER GROUPS ALONG THE WAY,

11:03.543 --> 11:04.995
YOU KNOW, FOR THE SNACKS,

11:04.995 --> 11:06.837
BUT IT WAS MORE ABOUT
REALLY COMMITTING TO SOMETHING

11:06.837 --> 11:08.418
AND FOLLOWING IT
THROUGH TO THE END.

11:08.418 --> 11:10.340
AND THEN
I GOT HIT BY A TRUCK.

11:11.461 --> 11:14.214
OKAY, THE FEMUR FRACTURE
MUST HAVE TRANSECTED
THE FEMORAL ARTERY.
Owen: WHOA.

11:14.214 --> 11:16.056
THAT'S WHY
HE'S SO HYPOTENSIVE.

11:16.056 --> 11:18.098
HE IS LOSING ALL
HIS BLOOD VOLUME INTO HIS THIGH.
MM-HMM.

11:18.098 --> 11:19.559
FOOT IS PULSELESS
AND COLD.

11:19.559 --> 11:21.601
WE NEED TO DO AN ANGIO
IN THE O.R. LET'S MOVE NOW.

11:21.601 --> 11:23.183
I MEAN,
THEY SCREWED HER!

11:23.183 --> 11:24.935
AND I WAS READY
TO MAKE A SCENE,

11:24.935 --> 11:26.807
BUT SHE JUST SAT THERE
IN HER SEAT.

11:26.807 --> 11:29.309
SHE CLAPPED FOR HIM.
SHE APPLAUDED HIM, DEREK!

11:29.309 --> 11:30.400
NO, GO AHEAD.
GET IT OUT.

11:30.400 --> 11:31.651
AND NOW I CAN'T EVEN
GET AHOLD OF HER.

11:31.651 --> 11:33.193
I MEAN, SHE COULD STILL BE
IN BOSTON.

11:33.193 --> 11:36.026
SHE COULD BE IN MEXICO.
I HAVE NO IDEA WHERE --

11:36.026 --> 11:38.779
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES ]
SHE'S IN O.R. 1.
THANK GOD!

11:41.321 --> 11:43.243
IS THAT
A SPINAL SCHWANNOMA?

11:43.243 --> 11:45.625
IT IS.
EXTENDED
INTO THE RETROPLEURAL SPACE?

11:45.625 --> 11:46.456
MM-HMM.

11:47.667 --> 11:48.829
IS THAT FOR ME?

11:48.829 --> 11:50.290
WE'RE OVERDUE
FOR A DATE.

11:50.290 --> 11:54.254
O.R. 3, YOU IN FRESH SCRUBS,
ME IN A FERRY-BOAT SCRUB CAP.

11:54.254 --> 11:55.505
YOU IN?

11:55.505 --> 11:57.547
WELL, THIS COULD TAKE HOURS.
WHAT ABOUT THE KIDS?

11:57.547 --> 11:59.259
AMY'S WITH THEM.
WE HAVE
A BABYSITTER NAMED AMY?

11:59.259 --> 12:01.101
AMY MY SISTER.
THE JUNKIE?

12:01.101 --> 12:02.682
SHE'S A RECOVERING ADDICT,
AND SHE LOVES KIDS.

12:02.682 --> 12:04.264
I'VE ONLY BEEN GONE
A DAY.

12:04.264 --> 12:06.226
THE TUMOR INVOLVES
THE GREAT VESSELS.

12:09.309 --> 12:10.901
I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.
MM-HMM.

12:10.901 --> 12:12.272
AND IT'S WORKING.

12:12.272 --> 12:13.483
MM-HMM.
[ LAUGHS ]

12:13.483 --> 12:15.655
YEAH, HIS FEMUR'S TOAST.
HE'LL NEED AN EX-FIX.

12:15.655 --> 12:17.157
SFA's TRANSECTED.

12:17.157 --> 12:18.738
OKAY. WE GOT TO RELIEVE
THE PRESSURE ON THIS LEG.

12:18.738 --> 12:19.990
Owen:
I JUST HEARD FROM GREY --

12:19.990 --> 12:21.952
CRISTINA'S IN O.R. 1,
DOING A HEART TRANSPLANT.

12:21.952 --> 12:23.784
KAREV AND ROBBINS
ARE WITH HER.

12:23.784 --> 12:25.495
HEY, WILSON, DID YOU HAPPEN
TO PUT ON BOOT COVERS
BEFORE YOU CAME IN HERE?

12:25.495 --> 12:27.247
Jo: WHY WOULD I --
[ GASPS ]

12:27.247 --> 12:29.129
[ OWEN LAUGHS ]

12:29.129 --> 12:31.331
OKAY. I GET IT.

12:31.331 --> 12:33.253
IT'S IN MY SOCKS.

12:33.253 --> 12:34.254
[ LAUGHTER ]

12:34.254 --> 12:36.506
OH!
THAT NEVER GETS OLD.

12:36.506 --> 12:39.719
[ LAUGHTER CONTINUES ]

12:39.719 --> 12:44.304
I JUST FEEL LIKE IT'S ONE THING
AFTER ANOTHER, AFTER ANOTHER.

12:44.304 --> 12:47.387
I DON'T KNOW HOW YOU DO IT
WITH THREE SICK KIDS.

12:47.387 --> 12:49.769
I'M BARELY KEEPING IT TOGETHER
WITH JUST ONE.

12:49.769 --> 12:51.521
[ KNOCKS ] TERESA?
HM?

12:51.521 --> 12:53.894
UH, DO YOU HAVE THOSE CONSENT
FORMS FOR THIS AFTERNOON?

12:53.894 --> 12:55.816
OH. YEAH, I FORGOT.
HANG ON.

12:55.816 --> 12:57.157
YEAH. TAKE YOUR TIME.

12:57.157 --> 13:00.360
I MEAN, YOU'RE THEIR PARENT.
YOU'RE WHO THEY TRUST.

13:00.360 --> 13:02.402
BUT YOU CAN'T
ACTUALLY HELP THEM.

13:02.402 --> 13:04.704
THAT'S THE DOCTOR'S JOB.

13:04.704 --> 13:07.787
THEN WEEKS GO BY,
AND ALL THIS...STUFF

13:07.787 --> 13:10.000
THAT'S SUPPOSED TO BE
MAKING THEM BETTER

13:10.000 --> 13:11.371
KEEPS NOT WORKING.

13:11.371 --> 13:13.834
AND I JUST --
I START TO WONDER,

13:13.834 --> 13:16.416
"DO THESE DOCTORS REALLY KNOW
WHAT'S BEST FOR MY KIDS?

13:16.416 --> 13:18.218
"AM I JUST
KIDDING MYSELF?

13:18.218 --> 13:19.920
WILL WE EVER GO HOME?"

13:19.920 --> 13:21.221
[ SIGHS ]

13:23.423 --> 13:25.385
SORRY, DOCTOR.
NO OFFENSE.

13:25.385 --> 13:27.767
NOPE. NONE TAKEN.

13:27.767 --> 13:29.429
UH, TERESA, I'M SORRY.

13:29.429 --> 13:31.351
YOU JUST HAVE
A COUPLE MORE TO SIGN.

13:31.351 --> 13:33.773
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

13:37.357 --> 13:39.739
REMOVING CROSS CLAMP
TO RE-ESTABLISH BLOOD FLOW.

13:39.739 --> 13:42.402
I DON'T SEE ONE TEAR, ONE LEAK.
YOU DID IT PERFECTLY.

13:42.402 --> 13:45.365
I MEAN, I'VE REALLY NEVER SEEN
SUCH AN EFFICIENT ANASTOMOSIS.

13:45.365 --> 13:46.496
LOOK, KAREV.
AWESOME JOB, YANG.

13:48.208 --> 13:50.250
INSPIRING.
FLAWLESS.

13:50.250 --> 13:51.371
CHARGE IT TO 20.

13:51.371 --> 13:52.582
[ WHIRRING ]

13:52.582 --> 13:54.334
[ BEEPING ]

13:54.334 --> 13:55.545
[ DEFIBRILLATOR SURGES ]

13:56.586 --> 13:59.089
SHOULD BE PUMPING
ANY MINUTE NOW.

13:59.089 --> 14:00.590
HOW LONG DOES IT TAKE?

14:00.590 --> 14:02.262
USUALLY, IT'S PRETTY MUCH RIGHT
AFTER RESTORING BLOOD FLOW,

14:02.262 --> 14:03.884
SO EYES ON THE FIELD.

14:03.884 --> 14:05.345
THIS IS NOT SOMETHING
YOU WANT TO MISS

14:05.345 --> 14:06.846
ON YOUR FIRST TRANSPLANT.

14:14.434 --> 14:16.856
SO...

14:16.856 --> 14:19.739
SHOULDN'T IT BE CONTRACTING
BY NOW?

14:19.739 --> 14:20.820
DR. YANG?

14:20.820 --> 14:22.192
STARTING CARDIAC MASSAGE.

14:22.192 --> 14:23.783
PACING WIRES NOW.
GET ME INTRACARDIAC EPI.

14:25.615 --> 14:27.197
COME ON, COME ON, COME ON.
BEAT.

14:31.912 --> 14:33.043
WHAT'S UNOS SAYING?

14:33.043 --> 14:34.254
WE'RE WAITING
ON A CALL BACK.

14:34.254 --> 14:35.375
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
HOW DOES THAT HAPPEN?

14:35.375 --> 14:36.997
THEY SENT US
A FREAKING LEMON HEART.

14:36.997 --> 14:38.838
THEY MUST HAVE INJURED
IT WHEN THEY WERE MOVING
IT FROM THE DONOR.

14:38.838 --> 14:40.170
[ CLATTER ]

14:40.170 --> 14:41.922
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

14:41.922 --> 14:44.764
IT'S UNOS. THEY'VE LOCATED
ANOTHER HEART THAT'S A MATCH.

14:44.764 --> 14:46.846
IT'S IN PORTLAND.
HOW OFTEN
DOES THAT HAPPEN?

14:46.846 --> 14:48.268
Arizona:
KAREV AND I WILL GO GET IT.
WE CAN'T RISK ANOTHER SCREW-UP.

14:48.268 --> 14:50.220
WELL, BOTH OF US
DON'T NEED TO --
NOW. LET'S GO.

14:50.220 --> 14:51.891
CRISTINA, YOU OKAY?
YEAH.

14:51.891 --> 14:53.853
DR. YANG, FRANKIE'S ALREADY BEEN
ON BYPASS FOR HOURS.

14:53.853 --> 14:56.106
AND SHE'S GONNA STAY ON IT.
KEEP MONITORING HER.

14:56.106 --> 14:57.357
PAGE ME
IF ANYTHING CHANGES.

14:59.899 --> 15:00.860
ALL RIGHT.

15:00.860 --> 15:02.112
THAT'S IT.

15:02.112 --> 15:03.693
SHALL WE?

15:03.693 --> 15:05.946
YOU REALLY THOUGHT
I WOULD COME HERE

15:05.946 --> 15:09.029
AND QUESTION WHY YANG DIDN'T GET
A HARPER AVERY?

15:09.029 --> 15:12.622
WELL, YOU'RE A PROUD PAPA.
SHE'S YOUR PRIZE STUDENT.

15:12.622 --> 15:14.334
I KNOW
IT'S IMPORTANT TO YOU.

15:14.334 --> 15:16.957
I-IT'S IMPORTANT
TO THE WHOLE HOSPITAL.

15:16.957 --> 15:18.748
AND YOU'RE AN INVESTOR
IN THAT HOSPITAL,

15:18.748 --> 15:20.380
SO I THINK IT'D BE IMPORTANT
TO YOU, TOO.

15:20.380 --> 15:21.921
IT IS.

15:21.921 --> 15:23.923
THAT'S WHY IT'S GOOD THAT THERE
IS AN IMPARTIAL COMMITTEE.

15:23.923 --> 15:26.006
[ CHUCKLES ]
WELL...

15:26.006 --> 15:26.886
"WELL" WHAT?

15:26.886 --> 15:29.509
IT'S NOT THAT IMPARTIAL.

15:29.509 --> 15:33.473
LOOK, IT MAKES NO SENSE
THAT SHE LOST.

15:33.473 --> 15:35.935
SEE, I READ HER PAPER, I READ
EVERY OTHER NOMINATED PAPER.

15:35.935 --> 15:37.557
THERE'S NO COMPARISON --

15:37.557 --> 15:40.270
UNLESS THERE WAS
SOME STATISTICAL
CALCULATION SHE BLEW,

15:40.270 --> 15:43.984
SOME GROSS ERROR
BURIED WAY DOWN IN THE DATA.

15:43.984 --> 15:45.695
YOU KNOW AS WELL AS I DO

15:45.695 --> 15:47.867
NONE OF THEM EVEN HOLDS A CANDLE
TO WHAT YANG'S BEEN DOING.

15:51.531 --> 15:53.953
NUMBER ONE,
I'M GLAD YOU'RE ALIVE.

15:53.953 --> 15:56.036
NUMBER TWO,
WHO DO YOU WANT ME TO GO AFTER?

15:56.036 --> 15:58.038
BECAUSE
I'M IN YOUR CORNER.
MER. [ SIGHS ]

15:58.038 --> 16:00.040
BUT I CAN'T BE IN YOUR CORNER
IF YOU DISAPPEAR ON ME.
MER, NOT NOW.

16:00.040 --> 16:02.042
Nurse: DR. YANG, THEY'RE ASKING
FOR YOU IN THE CCU.

16:02.042 --> 16:03.793
IVY McNEIL'S SATS
DROPPED BELOW 70.

16:07.007 --> 16:09.429
[ MONITORS BEEPING RAPIDLY ]
DR. YANG. YOU'RE BACK.
THANK GOD.

16:11.051 --> 16:13.013
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

16:13.013 --> 16:14.974
IVY'S HEART IS FAILING.

16:14.974 --> 16:16.476
SHE HAS A LOT OF FLUID
IN HER LUNGS.

16:16.476 --> 16:17.897
I NEED TO INTUBATE
RIGHT AWAY.

16:17.897 --> 16:20.020
PREPARE FOR RSI WITH
15 OF ETOMIDATE AND 10 OF VEC.

16:20.020 --> 16:23.233
LINK.
LINK, DON'T LOOK, BUDDY.

16:25.655 --> 16:28.868
[ Voice breaking ]
I'M HERE, HONEY.

16:28.868 --> 16:30.070
PUSH ETOMIDATE.

16:30.070 --> 16:31.951
Meredith: I BARELY
GOT TWO WORDS OUT OF HER.

16:31.951 --> 16:33.783
SHE'S OBVIOUSLY NOT OKAY,
RIGHT?

16:33.783 --> 16:35.995
Derek: YOU SAID SHE GOT
PULLED INTO AN EMERGENCY.

16:35.995 --> 16:37.827
I'M SURE SHE'S FINE.

16:37.827 --> 16:39.669
YOU KNOW, THIS IS THE MOST TIME
WE'VE SPENT TOGETHER,

16:39.669 --> 16:41.041
JUST THE TWO OF US,
IN WEEKS.

16:41.041 --> 16:42.082
IT'S REALLY NICE.

16:42.082 --> 16:44.044
WE HAVE TO DO IT
MORE OFTEN.

16:44.044 --> 16:45.505
GREY?

16:45.505 --> 16:47.427
SHOULD HAVE LEFT A TIE
ON THE DOOR.

16:47.427 --> 16:49.389
ABOUT
YOUR PORTAL VEIN PROJECT --

16:49.389 --> 16:51.801
DO YOU REALLY NEED LAB STAFF
FIVE DAYS A WEEK?

16:51.801 --> 16:53.763
Yes. Say yes.
YES. WHY?

16:53.763 --> 16:55.555
THE FOUNDATION
IS TRIMMING RESEARCH.
WHAT?!

16:55.555 --> 16:56.936
NO, NO, NO.
THEY'RE JUST LOOKING --
THE HELL THEY ARE --

16:56.936 --> 16:58.228
THE HARPER AVERY FOUNDATION

16:58.228 --> 16:59.689
DOESN'T MAKE ANY DECISIONS
ABOUT THIS HOSPITAL.

16:59.689 --> 17:01.191
IF THERE'S ONE THING

17:01.191 --> 17:03.523
THE HARPER AVERY FOUNDATION
CAN'T DO WELL,

17:03.523 --> 17:05.105
IT'S DECIDE
WHO SHOULD GET SOMETHING.

17:05.105 --> 17:06.566
OKAY, I AM JUST --

17:06.566 --> 17:08.858
TELL THEM THAT IF THEY CUT
MY FUNDING, I CUT THEIR TIRES.

17:08.858 --> 17:10.950
CRISTINA YANG
DESERVED THAT AWARD,

17:10.950 --> 17:13.032
NOT DR. NOBODY SUCKSALOT
FROM HOPKINS.

17:13.032 --> 17:16.326
AND TELL THEM IN SHORT SENTENCES
WITH LITTLE, TINY WORDS,

17:16.326 --> 17:19.079
BECAUSE THEY ARE BONEHEADS!

17:19.079 --> 17:21.040
[ SUCTION ]

17:21.040 --> 17:23.583
[ SIGHS ] AND WE WERE HAVING
SO MUCH FUN.

17:23.583 --> 17:26.506
April: JACKSON AND I
AREN'T HAVING JUST A FIGHT.

17:26.506 --> 17:28.088
THIS IS IMPORTANT --
IT'S NOT SOMETHING

17:28.088 --> 17:31.010
THAT CAN BE JUST GLOSSED OVER,
IGNORED, OR FIXED.

17:31.010 --> 17:33.303
IT -- I CAN'T PRETEND
LIKE NOTHING'S WRONG.

17:33.303 --> 17:35.054
Callie:
YEAH, I KNOW. I KNOW.

17:35.054 --> 17:36.726
YOU SAID ALL THAT
LAST NIGHT,

17:36.726 --> 17:39.309
THEN AGAIN THIS MORNING
OVER BREAKFAST.

17:39.309 --> 17:41.811
[ Chuckling ] AND NOW --
YOU'RE SAYING IT ALL AGAIN NOW.

17:41.811 --> 17:43.062
HEY. WOW.
LOOK AT THAT.

17:43.062 --> 17:44.854
HIS EX-FIX REALLY LOOKS
READY TO GO.

17:44.854 --> 17:46.486
SADLY, I THINK
OUR WORK IS DONE HERE.

17:46.486 --> 17:49.649
W-W-WHA-- Y-Y-Y-YOU'RE LEAVING?
Y-YOU'RE NOT LEAVING.

17:49.649 --> 17:51.741
DON'T WE NEED TO REVIEW
THE MEASUREMENTS WITH IMAGING?

17:51.741 --> 17:53.072
NO, WE DO. WE DO.
UH, IT'S JUST --

17:53.072 --> 17:54.784
WE SHOULD REALLY STAY OUT
OF KEPNER AND HUNT'S WAY,

17:54.784 --> 17:56.406
SO WE'RE GONNA DO IT
IN RADIOLOGY,

17:56.406 --> 17:58.458
WHERE THERE ARE BIGGER SCREENS
AND BETTER LIGHTING. SOUND GOOD?

17:58.458 --> 17:59.959
WELL, WE'RE ALMOST DONE
HERE, SO...

17:59.959 --> 18:01.791
N-- TAKE YOUR TIME.
LET'S GO, WILSON.

18:01.791 --> 18:03.253
[ SIGHS ]

18:03.253 --> 18:05.415
Teresa: WE SHOULD TAKE HIM HOME!
LET HIM GET BETTER!

18:05.415 --> 18:07.257
LET THIS TREATMENT
GET MORE ESTABLISHED!

18:07.257 --> 18:08.838
WE DON'T HAVE TO BE
THE GUINEA PIG!

18:08.838 --> 18:10.920
BUT THE TREATMENT
CAN BRING US OUR SON BACK.

18:10.920 --> 18:12.552
HE CAN LIVE
A NORMAL LIFE.

18:12.552 --> 18:13.763
OR IT COULD KILL HIM!

18:13.763 --> 18:16.766
THEY SAY IT WON'T,
BUT THIS THERAPY

18:16.766 --> 18:18.017
IS MADE WITH HIV.

18:18.017 --> 18:18.928
THAT DOESN'T
FREAK YOU OUT?

18:18.928 --> 18:19.979
IT'S DEACTIVATED!

18:19.979 --> 18:21.351
DO YOU EVEN KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS?!

18:21.351 --> 18:22.892
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS?

18:22.892 --> 18:25.024
EXCUSE ME. I NEED TO DO
ONE FINAL BLOOD TEST ON BRADEN.

18:25.024 --> 18:27.106
NO! NO MORE BLOOD DRAWS!
NO MORE INJECTIONS!

18:27.106 --> 18:28.728
NOTHING ELSE!
WE'RE DONE!

18:28.728 --> 18:30.860
THIS TREATMENT IS TOO MUCH!
IT'S KILLING HIM!

18:30.860 --> 18:32.732
OKAY, TERESA, LOOK,
I KNOW THAT YOU'RE SCARED.

18:32.732 --> 18:34.033
TERESA --

18:34.033 --> 18:36.366
NO, TELL DR. BAILEY
WE HAVE CHANGED OUR MINDS.

18:36.366 --> 18:38.998
YOU'RE NOT INJECTING BRADEN
WITH ANYTHING TODAY. YOU GOT IT?

18:42.832 --> 18:44.744
[ DING ]

18:44.744 --> 18:46.296
THE LAST TIME
THAT WE WERE ON A PLANE --

18:46.296 --> 18:48.668
CAN WE NOT TALK
ABOUT THE LAST TIME
YOU WERE ON A PLANE?

18:48.668 --> 18:50.250
NO. [ SIGHS ]

18:50.250 --> 18:52.342
ALEX, THE LAST TIME THAT
WE WERE ON A PLANE TOGETHER --

18:52.342 --> 18:53.753
THE FIRST TIME WE MET.

18:53.753 --> 18:56.135
LOOK, I KNOW
YOU BROUGHT ME ON THIS PLANE

18:56.135 --> 18:58.308
TO TALK ME OUT OF
TAKING THIS JOB.

18:58.308 --> 19:00.099
WE'LL BE IN PORTLAND SOON.

19:00.099 --> 19:02.312
JUST GET IT OVER WITH
AND SAY WHAT YOU'RE GONNA SAY.

19:02.312 --> 19:03.893
IT'S NOT LIKE
I CAN GO ANYWHERE.

19:03.893 --> 19:06.316
WE WERE ON OUR WAY
TO PICK UP A LIVER

19:06.316 --> 19:07.937
AND A SMALL BOWEL
FOR A 10-YEAR-OLD --

19:07.937 --> 19:09.229
AND NOW YOU THINK
I'M SELLING OUT,

19:09.229 --> 19:11.030
THAT I'M CHOOSING MONEY
OVER SUBSTANCE,

19:11.030 --> 19:12.942
AND THAT IT'S A WASTE
OF MY TALENT OR WHATEVER --

19:12.942 --> 19:14.153
THAT THERE'S MORE TO LIFE

19:14.153 --> 19:15.945
THAN NICE SCHEDULES
AND A BIG, FAT PAYCHECK.

19:15.945 --> 19:17.537
WELL,
I'VE THOUGHT ABOUT IT HARD.

19:17.537 --> 19:19.699
YOU'VE BEEN AWESOME,
BUT I'VE ALREADY STAYED
HERE ONCE FOR YOU.

19:19.699 --> 19:22.452
I HAVE TO START THINKING
ABOUT MYSELF, ABOUT WHAT I WANT.

19:22.452 --> 19:24.043
I'VE WORKED HARD,
AND I DESERVE THIS.

19:24.043 --> 19:26.836
I DESERVE TO THINK ABOUT MYSELF
FOR ONCE, OKAY?

19:26.836 --> 19:28.628
[ SIGHS ]

19:32.422 --> 19:34.214
Leah:
YANG IS A ROBOT.

19:34.214 --> 19:36.466
IF I JUST LOST THE HARPER AVERY,
I'D BE AWOL,

19:36.466 --> 19:38.258
IN MY BED
WITH A BOTTLE OF SCOTCH.

19:38.258 --> 19:42.262
ALTHOUGH, SHE DID JUST THROW
PICKUPS ACROSS A CROWDED O.R.

19:42.262 --> 19:43.973
YANG'S A SURGEON.

19:43.973 --> 19:46.185
SHE CARES MORE ABOUT
HER PATIENTS THAN STUPID AWARDS.

19:46.185 --> 19:48.187
WHAT'S THE LATEST A.B.G.?

19:48.187 --> 19:50.810
UH, PH IS 7.15,

19:50.810 --> 19:52.021
pCO2 IS 52.

19:52.021 --> 19:53.653
CRAP. SHE'S ACIDOTIC.

19:53.653 --> 19:54.984
PUSH BICARB
AND INCREASE HER SWEEP.

19:54.984 --> 19:56.406
OKAY.
OKAY, GOOD. GOOD.

19:56.406 --> 19:57.737
SHANE, SHE'S BLEEDING.

19:57.737 --> 19:58.908
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

19:58.908 --> 20:00.620
IT'S COMING
FROM ONE OF THE SUTURE LINES.

20:00.620 --> 20:02.322
PAGE DR. YANG NOW!

20:02.322 --> 20:04.374
IVY'S LUNGS ARE DOING BETTER
AFTER THE INTUBATION,

20:04.374 --> 20:06.205
BUT I NEED TO PLACE
A SPECIAL LINE

20:06.205 --> 20:07.877
TO GET A MORE ACCURATE
MEASUREMENT OF HER HEART.

20:07.877 --> 20:09.919
YOU MAY WANT TO LEAVE
DURING THIS PROCEDURE.

20:09.919 --> 20:11.210
NO. I'M STAYING.
I WANT TO STAY.

20:11.210 --> 20:13.002
YOU RAN IN HERE AFTER
FRANKIE'S SURGERY. IS SHE --

20:13.002 --> 20:15.925
THERE WAS A...COMPLICATION
WITH FRANKIE'S DONOR HEART,

20:15.925 --> 20:18.007
BUT A SECOND ONE
HAS BEEN LOCATED,

20:18.007 --> 20:19.599
AND IT'S ON ITS WAY.

20:19.599 --> 20:21.341
I JUST WANTED TO KEEP FRANKIE
IN THE O.R. UNTIL IT ARRIVES.

20:21.341 --> 20:23.263
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]
WHAT? IS -- IS THAT SAFE?
IS SHE GONNA BE OKAY?

20:23.263 --> 20:24.684
SHE'S BEING
CLOSELY MONITORED.

20:24.684 --> 20:26.145
DR. YANG,

20:26.145 --> 20:28.227
DR. ROSS AND DR. MURPHY
ARE ON THE PHONE FROM O.R. 1.

20:31.190 --> 20:32.812
PUT THEM ON SPEAKER.

20:32.812 --> 20:34.023
[ TELEPHONE BEEPS ]

20:34.023 --> 20:35.985
ROSS, UPDATE ME.
I'M HERE WITH FRANKIE'S DAD.

20:35.985 --> 20:38.237
SHANE: Frankie's bleeding
from one of her suture lines.

20:38.237 --> 20:40.280
and she's really acidotic.

20:40.280 --> 20:41.821
JOHN,
YOU SHOULD STEP OUT.
I'M STAYING.

20:44.744 --> 20:47.126
ROSS,
DID YOU PUSH BICARB?
We did.

20:47.126 --> 20:49.078
HOW ARE HER COAGS?
Stable, but this bleed
isn't slowing down.

20:49.078 --> 20:50.540
OKAY, WELL, YOU NEED
TO STOP THAT BLEEDING.

20:50.540 --> 20:52.462
IF SHE CONTINUES
TO BLEED --

20:52.462 --> 20:54.043
The triad of death --
We know.

20:54.043 --> 20:55.835
I'm so sorry, sir.

20:55.835 --> 20:58.177
OKAY, THROW
A HORIZONTAL MATTRESS STITCH,

20:58.177 --> 20:59.969
BUT CAREFUL
WITH HER TISSUES.

20:59.969 --> 21:02.762
THEY'RE EXTREMELY FRIABLE,
SO SOFT HANDS.

21:02.762 --> 21:04.804
YOU'RE ON THE RIGHT SIDE
OF THE TABLE.

21:04.804 --> 21:06.886
CRISTINA:
You have one chance, or else
you could rip through the aorta,

21:06.886 --> 21:08.978
which is essential to connecting
the new heart when it arrives.

21:08.978 --> 21:10.189
NOPE. [ SIGHS ]

21:10.189 --> 21:12.021
Just take a breath,
just throw the stitch.

21:12.021 --> 21:13.393
YOU CAN DO THIS.

21:13.393 --> 21:15.104
I'VE NEVER PUT
A HORIZONTAL MATTRESS

21:15.104 --> 21:16.946
IN AN AORTA BEFORE --
ONLY IN A BOWEL.

21:16.946 --> 21:19.529
FROM THIS SIDE, I'LL JUST
TEAR THROUGH HER NATIVE AORTA.

21:19.529 --> 21:21.741
WELL, WHAT IF
I TEAR THROUGH IT?
YOU WON'T!

21:21.741 --> 21:23.903
YOU CAN DO THIS.

21:23.903 --> 21:25.074
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

21:34.674 --> 21:36.676
ROSS! MURPHY!

21:39.919 --> 21:41.841
SHANE: We got it.
We stopped the bleed.

21:41.841 --> 21:42.972
SHE'S FINE.

21:42.972 --> 21:44.924
[ SIGHS ]
THEY'RE BOTH FINE.

21:49.349 --> 21:51.190
Richard:
SHE GETS RESULTS.

21:51.190 --> 21:54.273
SHE ALWAYS HAS,
AND THIS IS NO EXCEPTION.

21:54.273 --> 21:55.935
M-MAKE ME UNDERSTAND,

21:55.935 --> 21:58.488
BECAUSE MY READ IS THAT
YANG SHOULD HAVE CLEARLY WON.

21:58.488 --> 22:00.029
I MEAN,
WHAT AM I MISSING?

22:00.029 --> 22:01.821
FROM WHERE I'M STANDING,
SHE HAD IT BY A MILE.

22:01.821 --> 22:03.993
RICHARD, HONESTLY,
TELL ME YOU'RE NOT THIS NAIVE.

22:03.993 --> 22:05.825
WELL, WHAT IS THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

22:05.825 --> 22:07.036
THE HARPER AVERY FOUNDATION

22:07.036 --> 22:09.709
CO-OWNS THE HOSPITAL
CRISTINA YANG WORKS FOR.

22:10.870 --> 22:13.413
SHE COULD NEVER
WIN THAT AWARD.

22:21.551 --> 22:22.842
I DON'T KNOW HOW LONG
THIS STITCH IS GONNA HOLD.

22:22.842 --> 22:24.343
PH AND BICARB?
Man: 7.0 AND 14.

22:24.343 --> 22:25.925
DR. YANG, NOW SHE'S OOZING
FROM THE IVC.

22:25.925 --> 22:27.467
I SEE IT, SHANE.
AREN'T WE GONNA
PUT IN A SUTURE?

22:27.467 --> 22:28.598
IF WE JUST KEEP
THROWING IN STITCHES,

22:28.598 --> 22:29.889
SHE'LL DISSECT
ALL OVER THE PLACE.

22:29.889 --> 22:31.471
WE HAVE TO GET FRANKIE
OFF THIS TABLE.

22:31.471 --> 22:32.642
Leah: HOW?
SHE'S GETTING A TRANSPLANT.

22:32.642 --> 22:34.313
IN THIS STATE,
SHE'LL NEVER SURVIVE IT.

22:34.313 --> 22:35.775
FIRST,
SHE GETS A LEMON HEART,

22:35.775 --> 22:37.186
AND NOW WE DON'T KNOW
IF THE NEW ONE'S GONNA MAKE IT?

22:37.186 --> 22:39.238
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]
WAIT. IS THAT ROBBINS?

22:39.238 --> 22:40.400
How we doing?

22:40.400 --> 22:42.281
THE HEART IS OUT,
AND WE'RE ON THE MOVE.

22:42.281 --> 22:44.033
[ TELEPHONE BEEPS ]

22:47.657 --> 22:49.449
WANT TO LET
THE COORDINATOR KNOW?

22:49.449 --> 22:51.701
OH. PHONE THE PILOT.
LET HIM KNOW WE'RE ON OUR WAY.

22:54.333 --> 22:55.995
SO, THIS IS
HOW IT'S GONNA BE NOW?

22:55.995 --> 22:57.547
RADIO SILENCE
TILL THE END OF MY FELLOWSHIP?

22:57.547 --> 22:58.628
THAT'S HOW
YOU'RE GONNA LEAVE THINGS?

23:01.591 --> 23:04.053
ALEX,
I BROUGHT YOU HERE TODAY

23:04.053 --> 23:07.597
BECAUSE I TRUSTED YOUR SKILLS
TO PROPERLY PROCURE THIS HEART.

23:07.597 --> 23:10.890
AND THEN WE GOT ON THAT PLANE,
AND I STARTED FEELING SAD

23:10.890 --> 23:13.102
BECAUSE YOU'RE LEAVING SOON
AND I WILL MISS YOU.

23:13.102 --> 23:14.894
I DIDN'T BRING YOU TODAY
TO SCOLD YOU.

23:14.894 --> 23:16.896
I'M PROUD OF YOU
AND I'M HAPPY FOR YOU,

23:16.896 --> 23:19.108
AND ALL I WANTED WAS TO SHARE
A FREAKING MEMORY, OKAY?

23:19.108 --> 23:20.650
I WAS BEING SENTIMENTAL!

23:22.732 --> 23:23.863
OH.

23:26.526 --> 23:27.737
[ LATCHES CLICK ]

23:27.737 --> 23:29.158
YOU KNOW,
IF I TAKE THE JOB,

23:29.158 --> 23:30.910
I'M STILL GONNA HAVE
HOSPITAL PRIVILEGES.

23:30.910 --> 23:32.331
YOU'LL SEE ME AROUND.

23:32.331 --> 23:34.534
SHUT UP, KAREV.
MOMENT'S RUINED.

23:37.877 --> 23:40.920
Owen:
JUST A FEW MORE SUTURES.

23:40.920 --> 23:42.962
YOU KNOW WHERE HE WAS
WHEN HE GOT HIT?

23:42.962 --> 23:45.094
HE WAS CROSSING
HIGHWAY 519.

23:45.094 --> 23:46.806
HE COULD SEE THE WATER.

23:46.806 --> 23:49.679
ALL HE WANTED TO DO
WAS WALK FROM OCEAN TO OCEAN.

23:49.679 --> 23:51.931
[ Voice breaking ]
HE WAS JUST SO FREAKING CLOSE.

23:53.142 --> 23:54.433
OKAY,
LET'S CHECK THE PULSE.

23:54.433 --> 23:56.015
IT'S NOT FAIR,
YOU KNOW?

23:56.015 --> 23:58.147
YOU MAKE A COMMITMENT,
IT'S SUPPOSED TO MEAN SOMETHING,

23:58.147 --> 24:00.610
AND THEN A...PICKUP TRUCK
JUST TAKES YOU OUT.

24:02.732 --> 24:05.194
[ CRYING ]

24:05.194 --> 24:06.776
HEY, YOU OKAY?

24:08.407 --> 24:10.199
[ Crying ]
S-- SORRY.

24:11.621 --> 24:13.072
I JUST F-FEEL LIKE

24:13.072 --> 24:16.666
THIS FIGHT WITH JACKSON
IS, LIKE, THE FIGHT,

24:16.666 --> 24:18.337
AND I...

24:18.337 --> 24:21.881
I DON'T KNOW
HOW WE RECOVER FROM IT.

24:23.963 --> 24:25.044
LISTEN.

24:25.044 --> 24:26.716
[ SIGHS ]

24:26.716 --> 24:28.888
SOME FIGHTS,
YOU JUST CAN'T GET PAST.

24:28.888 --> 24:30.850
[ SNIFFLES ]
YOU KNOW?

24:30.850 --> 24:33.553
LIKE ME AND CRISTINA, IT WAS --
IT WAS ABOUT KIDS.

24:33.553 --> 24:36.596
YOU AND AVERY?

24:36.596 --> 24:38.858
THIS IS
YOUR FIRST FIGHT.

24:38.858 --> 24:40.019
YOU WILL GET PAST THIS,

24:40.019 --> 24:41.901
AND THEN SOMETHING ELSE
WILL COME ALONG,

24:41.901 --> 24:44.023
[ Chuckling ] AND YOU'LL FIGHT
ABOUT THAT, TOO.

24:44.023 --> 24:47.987
AND YOU GUYS WILL RECOVER
EVERY TIME.

24:49.949 --> 24:52.451
THIS IS NOT
YOUR PICKUP TRUCK.

24:54.874 --> 24:56.285
[ CHUCKLES, SNIFFLES ]

25:01.460 --> 25:03.462
[ WHIRRING ]

25:04.884 --> 25:06.926
NOW THAT IT'S THAWED,

25:06.926 --> 25:09.468
AND I'VE ADDED THE VIRUS
TO THE CULTURE,

25:09.468 --> 25:12.511
I JUST HAVE TO WASH THEM DOWN
AND GIVE HIM THE INJECTION

25:12.511 --> 25:14.513
WITHIN THE NEXT
FOUR TO SIX HOURS,

25:14.513 --> 25:16.345
AND THEN, THEORETICALLY,

25:16.345 --> 25:17.847
THAT'S WHEN
THE MAGIC WILL HAPPEN.

25:17.847 --> 25:19.689
SEE, THAT'S THE PROBLEM,
THOUGH, BAILEY.

25:19.689 --> 25:21.310
SO FAR, ALL OF THIS
IS THEORETICAL,

25:21.310 --> 25:23.102
AND THE FOUNDATION NEEDS
ACTUAL RESULTS.

25:23.102 --> 25:24.483
I NEED YOU
TO HELP ME OUT, OKAY?

25:24.483 --> 25:26.355
GIVE ME SOMETHING,
ANYTHING CONCRETE,

25:26.355 --> 25:28.527
THAT SHOWS THAT YOUR PROJECT
IS PRODUCING RESULTS.

25:28.527 --> 25:30.910
NO, D-- IT WILL BE.

25:30.910 --> 25:33.032
ONCE I GIVE
THIS TARGETED GENE THERAPY

25:33.032 --> 25:34.864
TO MY BUBBLE BOY,
I KNOW IT WILL.

25:34.864 --> 25:36.325
I-I CAN FEEL IT.

25:36.325 --> 25:38.618
OKAY, I CAN'T EXACTLY PITCH
THAT WE NEED TO KEEP YOUR LAB

25:38.618 --> 25:40.539
BECAUSE YOU HAVE A FEELING,
CAN I?

25:42.291 --> 25:44.333
YOU SAID
YOU'RE DOING THIS TODAY?

25:44.333 --> 25:45.464
YES, I AM.

25:45.464 --> 25:47.336
AND IT'S GOING TO WORK.

25:47.336 --> 25:50.549
DR. BAILEY,
DO YOU HAVE A MINUTE?

25:50.549 --> 25:52.301
YOU PURSUED HER.
YOU ENCOURAGED HER.

25:52.301 --> 25:54.173
YOU ALL BUT TOLD HER
SHE WAS A FRONT RUNNER,

25:54.173 --> 25:56.345
WHEN YOU KNEW SHE WAS
NOTHING BUT WINDOW DRESSING.

25:56.345 --> 25:58.347
SHE WAS NOT
WINDOW DRESSING!

25:58.347 --> 26:00.479
SHE WAS NOMINATED
FOR A PRESTIGIOUS AWARD

26:00.479 --> 26:02.812
THAT BROUGHT PUBLICITY
TO HER AND THE HOSPITAL.

26:02.812 --> 26:04.183
YOU USED HER!

26:04.183 --> 26:06.235
SHE WAS NEVER GONNA WIN
THAT DAMN THING FOR A SECOND.

26:06.235 --> 26:07.897
NOBODY
FROM GREY-SLOAN MEMORIAL

26:07.897 --> 26:10.650
WILL EVER WIN A HARPER AVERY,
WILL THEY -- EVER?

26:10.650 --> 26:12.361
DO YOU WANT ME
TO REMIND YOU

26:12.361 --> 26:14.744
WHY THERE IS
A GREY-SLOAN MEMORIAL HOSPITAL?

26:14.744 --> 26:17.536
OR SHOULD I JUST TAKE
MY $24 MILLION AND GO HOME?

26:19.078 --> 26:22.501
WHAT DRAWS ME TO YOU, RICHARD,
IS YOUR IDEALISM.

26:22.501 --> 26:25.705
I FIND IT
EXTREMELY ATTRACTIVE.

26:25.705 --> 26:27.707
BUT THIS IS BUSINESS.

26:27.707 --> 26:28.918
AND I DO NOT APPRECIATE

26:28.918 --> 26:30.589
YOUR COMING ALL THE WAY
ACROSS THE COUNTRY

26:30.589 --> 26:32.421
TO HARANGUE ME
ABOUT THE FACT

26:32.421 --> 26:34.513
THAT YOUR PRIZE PONY
DIDN'T GET A RIBBON!

26:34.513 --> 26:36.555
AND IF IT MAKES YOU
FEEL BETTER...

26:36.555 --> 26:38.638
SHE HAD THE VOTES.

26:44.023 --> 26:45.935
ARE YOU THAT NAIVE?

26:45.935 --> 26:49.859
CATHERINE, DO YOU REALLY THINK
THAT'S WHY I CAME ALL THIS WAY,

26:49.859 --> 26:53.532
WHY I PLANNED AN ENTIRE WEEKEND
WITH THE THINGS THAT YOU LOVE?

26:53.532 --> 26:55.534
RICHARD --
I MADE RESERVATIONS
AT CIPRIANI'S

26:55.534 --> 26:56.906
BECAUSE I KNOW
YOU LOVE IT THERE.

26:56.906 --> 26:59.078
AND I WAS GOING TO WAIT
UNTIL JUST BEFORE DESSERT

26:59.078 --> 27:01.661
AND THE WAITER WAS GONNA
BRING YOU A GLASS OF CHAMPAGNE,

27:01.661 --> 27:04.333
AND I WAS GOING TO TELL YOU
HOW MUCH I LOVE YOU

27:04.333 --> 27:06.916
AND HOW RIGHT FOR ONE ANOTHER
WE ARE,

27:06.916 --> 27:10.249
HOW YOU MAKE ME FEEL EXCITED
TO BE ALIVE,

27:10.249 --> 27:12.631
HOW YOU GIVE ME A REASON
TO GET UP EACH MORNING

27:12.631 --> 27:14.714
AND SAY A THANKFUL PRAYER
EVERY NIGHT.

27:14.714 --> 27:17.136
I WAS GONNA ASK YOU
TO BE BY MY SIDE

27:17.136 --> 27:18.597
FOR THE REST OF OUR LIVES.

27:19.969 --> 27:21.851
THAT'S WHY I'M HERE.

27:21.851 --> 27:24.643
THAT'S WHY I CAME.

27:40.489 --> 27:42.281
AND NOW I'M LEAVING.

27:47.336 --> 27:50.549
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

27:57.506 --> 27:59.098
Sabine:
I'M -- I'M SORRY. WHAT?

27:59.098 --> 28:00.559
YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO SAY --

28:00.559 --> 28:02.261
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO
SAY IT ALL AGAIN.

28:02.261 --> 28:05.564
DR. ROBBINS IS ON HER WAY
WITH A NEW HEART FOR FRANKIE,

28:05.564 --> 28:07.606
BUT IVY'S DETERIORATION
HAS CAUSED HER

28:07.606 --> 28:10.609
TO SHOOT UP TO THE TOP
OF THE TRANSPLANT LIST, TOO.

28:10.609 --> 28:14.693
IVY IS ALSO A PERFECT MATCH
FOR THE DONOR HEART EN ROUTE.

28:14.693 --> 28:16.655
BUT T-THAT'S
FRANKIE'S HEART.

28:16.655 --> 28:19.028
OFFICIALLY, YES,
BUT...

28:19.028 --> 28:23.532
UNDER THE CIRCUMSTANCES,
THE HEART COULD BE REDIRECTED.

28:23.532 --> 28:25.955
TO IVY?

28:25.955 --> 28:28.667
YOU W-- YOU WANT TO GIVE
FRANKIE'S HEART TO IVY?

28:28.667 --> 28:30.169
NO, I DON'T WANT --

28:32.631 --> 28:34.003
MEDICALLY SPEAKING,

28:34.003 --> 28:36.005
FRANKIE'S CONDITION
IS DECLINING RAPIDLY.

28:36.005 --> 28:39.388
TECHNICALLY,
IVY IS MORE STABLE,

28:39.388 --> 28:41.510
WHICH WOULD GIVE THE HEART
A BETTER CHANCE OF SURVIVAL.

28:41.510 --> 28:43.102
WAIT. JUST --

28:43.102 --> 28:45.014
BUT -- B-B-BUT
IF FRANKIE'S WORSE,

28:45.014 --> 28:47.186
DON'T YOU HAVE TO GIVE THE HEART
TO THE ONE THAT'S THE WORST?

28:47.186 --> 28:50.309
UNLESS SHE THINKS
IT'S A WASTE.

28:50.309 --> 28:52.441
YOU THINK THE HEART
WILL BE WASTED ON FRANKIE?

28:52.441 --> 28:53.983
I JUST WANT TO EXPLAIN
ALL YOUR OPTIONS.

28:53.983 --> 28:56.235
OUR OPTIONS?
THIS IS OUR DECISION?

28:56.235 --> 28:58.567
WAIT. YOU'RE --
YOU'RE ASKING US TO CHOOSE?

28:58.567 --> 29:01.070
YOU WANT US
TO TRY TO PICK

29:01.070 --> 29:03.242
WHICH OF OUR CHILDREN
GETS A HEART

29:03.242 --> 29:04.743
AND WHICH ONE DOESN'T?

29:04.743 --> 29:07.456
FRANKIE CAN BE FITTED WITH A
TOTAL ARTIFICIAL HEART FOR NOW.

29:07.456 --> 29:09.628
WE CAN'T CHOOSE.
YOU HAVE TO DO IT.

29:09.628 --> 29:12.461
WE HAVE THREE CHILDREN,
DR. YANG --

29:12.461 --> 29:15.714
THREE...AMAZING...

29:15.714 --> 29:20.259
[ Crying ]
BEAUTIFUL, KIND CHILDREN.

29:20.259 --> 29:21.640
AND WE CAN'T --

29:21.640 --> 29:25.474
WE CAN'T TRY AND PICK
BETWEEN TWO OF THEM.

29:25.474 --> 29:26.976
WE WON'T.

29:28.307 --> 29:30.689
YOU HAVE TO
MAKE THIS DECISION.

29:30.689 --> 29:33.442
PLEASE.

29:33.442 --> 29:35.024
PLEASE.

29:41.660 --> 29:43.532
THERE YOU ARE.

29:43.532 --> 29:44.824
[ SIGHS ]

29:44.824 --> 29:46.906
FRANKIE'S HEART
IS AS STIFF AS A ROCK,

29:46.906 --> 29:48.908
AND IVY'S GOT
GLOBAL SYSTOLIC DYSFUNCTION.

29:48.908 --> 29:50.749
IT'S ABSOLUTELY
IMPOSSIBLE.

29:50.749 --> 29:52.541
WHY DIDN'T YOU
CALL ME?

29:52.541 --> 29:54.543
[ SIGHS ] MER ALREADY
YELLED AT ME ABOUT THIS.

29:54.543 --> 29:56.625
I'M SORRY, OKAY?
I JUST --

29:56.625 --> 29:59.678
I WANTED TO BE ALONE,
SO I LEFT.

29:59.678 --> 30:01.590
I'M NOT TALKING ABOUT --
[ SIGHS ]

30:01.590 --> 30:03.182
I JUST HEARD
ABOUT THE McNEILS.

30:03.182 --> 30:06.805
YOU SHOULD HAVE CALLED ME
TO HELP YOU MAKE THIS DECISION.

30:06.805 --> 30:10.059
NO SURGEON SHOULD HAVE
TO MAKE A DECISION
LIKE THIS ON THEIR OWN.

30:10.059 --> 30:13.102
THAT'S WHY I'M HERE. THAT'S WHY
YOU HAVE A CHIEF OF SURGERY.

30:13.102 --> 30:14.934
THEY'RE MY PATIENTS.
I KNOW THEIR STATUS.

30:14.934 --> 30:16.145
I CAN DECIDE THIS.

30:16.145 --> 30:17.276
BUT YOU DON'T HAVE TO.

30:19.488 --> 30:20.649
YES, I DO.

30:30.950 --> 30:32.952
Cristina: PREPARE TO START
SECTIONING OFF THE VESSELS.

30:32.952 --> 30:34.623
IS THAT
A GUSTAFSON ARTIFICIAL HEART?

30:34.623 --> 30:36.125
WE'RE GETTING FRANKIE
OFF THIS TABLE IMMEDIATELY.

30:36.125 --> 30:38.167
AND THE HEART
THAT'S ON ITS WAY?

30:38.167 --> 30:40.169
WE'RE REALLOCATING THAT HEART.
IT'S GOING TO IVY.

30:40.169 --> 30:41.340
RUSSELL'S
PREPPING HER NOW.

30:41.340 --> 30:43.302
OKAY, LET'S MOVE.

30:43.302 --> 30:44.924
AMELIA: You guys
gonna be home for dinner?

30:44.924 --> 30:46.135
YEAH. SURE.
SOUNDS GOOD.

30:46.135 --> 30:47.096
Okay, awesome!
Can't wait!

30:47.096 --> 30:48.557
YEAH, NEITHER CAN WE.

30:48.557 --> 30:50.179
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]
DOES THAT MEAN
WHAT I THINK IT MEANS?

30:50.179 --> 30:51.971
THAT THERE'S GONNA BE DINNER
WAITING FOR US

30:51.971 --> 30:54.143
ON OUR DINING ROOM TABLE
WHEN WE GET HOME?

30:54.143 --> 30:55.935
HAVE WE EVER EVEN USED
OUR DINING ROOM TABLE?

30:55.935 --> 30:57.436
JUST REMIND ME
TO THANK MY SISTER

30:57.436 --> 30:59.528
FOR LETTING ME ACTUALLY SPEND
AN ENTIRE DAY WITH MY WIFE.

30:59.528 --> 31:01.320
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

31:01.320 --> 31:03.072
WELL, SHE'S NOT
A PERMANENT SOLUTION.

31:03.072 --> 31:05.034
AH, NOT YET,
BUT WE HAVE A SPARE BEDROOM.

31:05.034 --> 31:06.865
WE COULD GIVE HER
SURGICAL PRIVILEGES.

31:06.865 --> 31:08.617
THAT WOULD GIVE HER
LESS TIME FOR CHILDCARE.

31:08.617 --> 31:10.079
I KNOW IT'S NOT PERMANENT,

31:10.079 --> 31:12.912
BUT WE SPENT AN ENTIRE DAY
WITHOUT DROPPING ANY BALLS.

31:12.912 --> 31:14.914
YOU KNOW, MAYBE SHE'LL
EVEN PUT THE KIDS TO BED.

31:14.914 --> 31:16.705
MAYBE WE COULD HAVE
SOME WINE.

31:16.705 --> 31:18.918
YOU KNOW, AMY IS MAKING DINNER
FOR THE KIDS.

31:18.918 --> 31:21.130
MAYBE WE HAVE TIME
FOR A LITTLE MM-MM.

31:21.130 --> 31:23.052
IT WOULD BE A SHAME
TO END SUCH A GREAT DAY

31:23.052 --> 31:24.263
WITH NO DESSERT.

31:24.263 --> 31:25.764
[ SQUEALS ]

31:25.764 --> 31:28.177
Alex: WHY AREN'T YOU TRYING
TO TALK ME INTO STAYING?

31:28.177 --> 31:29.888
Arizona: OH, GOD.
ARE WE STILL ON THIS?

31:29.888 --> 31:31.140
CAN'T WE JUST FOCUS

31:31.140 --> 31:32.972
ON TRANSPLANTING THE HEART
WE JUST RETRIEVED?

31:32.972 --> 31:34.513
YEAH. NEVER MIND.
I'LL SHUT UP.

31:36.185 --> 31:38.147
OF COURSE
I WANT YOU TO STAY.

31:38.147 --> 31:40.229
BUT THIS SOUNDS LIKE
AN INCREDIBLE JOB OPPORTUNITY,

31:40.229 --> 31:42.821
AND YOU'RE RIGHT --
YOU DID STAY HERE FOR ME ONCE,

31:42.821 --> 31:44.193
AND I DON'T WANT
TO STAND IN YOUR WAY AGAIN,

31:44.193 --> 31:45.824
SO IF YOU WANT TO LEAVE,
YOU SHOULD LEAVE --

31:45.824 --> 31:48.197
BUT NOT BECAUSE OF SOMETHING
THAT I DO OR DON'T SAY.

31:48.197 --> 31:49.448
YOU SHOULD LEAVE

31:49.448 --> 31:51.330
BECAUSE THIS IS
THE NEXT BEST THING FOR YOU

31:51.330 --> 31:53.162
AND BECAUSE YOU'RE EXCITED
ABOUT THIS JOB

31:53.162 --> 31:55.164
AND YOU'RE READY
TO GO DO GREAT THINGS.

31:55.164 --> 31:56.665
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

31:56.665 --> 31:58.087
AND COLLECT
A BIG, FAT PAYCHECK.

31:58.087 --> 31:59.168
REALLY BIG.

31:59.168 --> 32:01.670
I GUESS YOU HAVE
A DECISION TO MAKE.

32:01.670 --> 32:03.342
DON'T SCREW THIS ONE UP.

32:03.342 --> 32:04.423
[ DOOR OPENS ]

32:05.965 --> 32:07.426
Owen: OKAY,
LET'S TRANSPORT HER.

32:07.426 --> 32:09.758
B.P.'s STABLE. I'M GONNA SEE
HOW RUSSELL'S DOING WITH IVY.

32:09.758 --> 32:11.010
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]
BRING IN THE BED.

32:11.010 --> 32:12.181
WHAT HAPPENED?

32:12.181 --> 32:13.392
VENTRICULAR PRESSURE'S
UP TO 200.

32:13.392 --> 32:14.473
SHE'S DISSECTING.

32:14.473 --> 32:15.934
NOW SHE'S PLUMMETED TO 15.
WHAT THE HELL?

32:15.934 --> 32:17.146
DAMN IT.
IT -- IT RUPTURED.

32:17.146 --> 32:18.557
OKAY, WE'RE GONNA
HAVE TO REOPEN HER.

32:18.557 --> 32:19.688
STAPLE REMOVER!

32:19.688 --> 32:21.190
I MEAN, THE THING
I DON'T UNDERSTAND IS,

32:21.190 --> 32:23.232
WON'T BRADEN DIE IF HE DOESN'T
GET THIS TREATMENT?

32:23.232 --> 32:24.653
IT'S POSSIBLE.

32:24.653 --> 32:26.235
SO...

32:26.235 --> 32:28.567
I MEAN, DOES THIS HAPPEN OFTEN
WITH EXPERIMENTAL TREATMENTS?

32:28.567 --> 32:30.069
THAT THE PARENTS
OR THE GUARDIANS

32:30.069 --> 32:31.120
JUST WITHDRAW
THEIR CONSENT?

32:31.120 --> 32:32.371
Please stop talking.

32:32.371 --> 32:33.572
AND THEN WHAT DO I DO

32:33.572 --> 32:35.244
WITH THESE CONSENT FORMS
SHE JUST SIGNED?

32:35.244 --> 32:37.336
I MEAN, DO I --
DO I SHRED THEM? DO I TOSS THEM?

32:37.336 --> 32:38.998
I TOLD YOU --
STOP TALKING!

32:38.998 --> 32:41.340
♪ WHAT HAS HAPPENED
TO IT ALL? ♪

32:41.340 --> 32:43.042
UH, I'LL TAKE CARE
OF THOSE.

32:43.042 --> 32:45.214
♪ CRAZY, SOME WOULD SAY ♪

32:45.214 --> 32:51.930
♪ WHERE IS THE LIFE
THAT I RECOGNIZE? ♪

32:51.930 --> 32:53.092
♪ IT'S GONE AWAY ♪

32:53.092 --> 32:57.146
♪ BUT I WON'T CRY
FOR YESTERDAY ♪

32:57.146 --> 33:01.060
♪ THERE'S AN ORDINARY WORLD ♪

33:01.060 --> 33:03.442
JUST GET ONE DAMN SUTURE
TO HOLD.

33:03.442 --> 33:04.653
HOW'S
HER VENTRICULAR PRESSURE?

33:04.653 --> 33:06.065
Shane: ZERO.

33:06.065 --> 33:07.196
PUPILS?

33:07.196 --> 33:09.608
FIXED AND NONREACTIVE.

33:09.608 --> 33:11.070
[ FLATLINE ]

33:11.070 --> 33:12.071
CRISTINA.

33:12.071 --> 33:13.612
WHAT?!

33:13.612 --> 33:16.245
CRISTINA, WE'VE BEEN AT THIS
FOR ALMOST AN HOUR.

33:16.245 --> 33:20.419
♪ WHEN I NEED YOU MOST? ♪

33:20.419 --> 33:22.041
♪ GONE AWAY ♪

33:22.041 --> 33:25.124
IVY'S TRANSPLANT
WENT PERFECTLY.

33:25.124 --> 33:27.756
HER POST-OP ECHO
IS COMPLETELY NORMAL.

33:27.756 --> 33:29.838
SHE SHOULD BE
AWAKE SOON.

33:29.838 --> 33:31.220
Jon: AND FRANKIE?

33:35.894 --> 33:37.726
NO.

33:37.726 --> 33:39.268
NO!

33:39.268 --> 33:41.600
I-IT CAN'T BE.

33:41.600 --> 33:43.852
[ SOBS ]

33:45.644 --> 33:47.025
[ Crying ] YOU...

33:48.147 --> 33:51.990
WELL, HOW --
HOW THE HELL DID THIS...

33:51.990 --> 33:53.742
WE TRUSTED YOU!

33:53.742 --> 33:56.865
WHAT THE HELL DID YOU DO
TO OUR CHILD?!

33:56.865 --> 33:58.707
WE ARE SO SORRY
FOR YOUR LOSS.

33:58.707 --> 34:00.329
OH, GOD!

34:00.329 --> 34:02.291
[ SOBBING ]

34:06.125 --> 34:08.837
[ Voice breaking ]
WE NEED TO BE WITH OUR KIDS.

34:15.884 --> 34:18.227
[ SIREN WAILS ]

34:18.227 --> 34:21.230
[ WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER P.A. ]

34:28.317 --> 34:29.738
YOUR STITCH HELD.

34:29.738 --> 34:30.779
SO?

34:32.651 --> 34:34.653
I'VE NEVER SEEN VESSELS
THAT FRIABLE,

34:34.653 --> 34:37.156
AND I'VE BEEN AROUND
A LOT OF DISEASED HEARTS.

34:37.156 --> 34:38.997
YOU DID
AN AMAZING THING.

34:38.997 --> 34:41.410
SHANE, THE KID DIED.

34:41.410 --> 34:43.041
IT WASN'T
ANYTHING YOU DID.

34:43.041 --> 34:46.755
♪ I WANT TO KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE THINKING ♪

34:46.755 --> 34:48.167
♪ THERE ARE SOME...♪

34:48.167 --> 34:50.169
Arizona: THEY WANT US TO BE
THE CENTER OF INNOVATION,

34:50.169 --> 34:52.551
BUT THEY DON'T WANT
TO PAY FOR IT.
THEY LOVE IT
WHEN WE INNOVATE.

34:52.551 --> 34:53.762
THEY NOMINATED YANG
FOR AN AWARD.

34:53.762 --> 34:55.214
SHE WAS ROBBED.
THEY'RE BONEHEADS.

34:55.214 --> 34:56.765
WE CAN'T GIVE WITH ONE HAND
AND TAKE WITH THE OTHER.

34:56.765 --> 34:58.096
WE HAVE TO STOP THIS.

34:58.096 --> 35:00.719
THERE'S NO STOPPING THIS.
GUYS, THEY OWN THE PLACE.

35:00.719 --> 35:02.851
WE ARE
JUST THEIR MANAGING BOARD.

35:02.851 --> 35:04.853
THIS CONVERSATION
IS OUR RELATIONSHIP NOW.

35:04.853 --> 35:07.816
BEST WE CAN DO IS TRY TO GUIDE
THEM TO MAKE THE RIGHT DECISION.

35:07.816 --> 35:09.488
THAT'S BY MAKING
OUR OWN DECISION,

35:09.488 --> 35:10.609
AS TOUGH AS THAT MIGHT BE.

35:10.609 --> 35:12.191
LOOK, THIS IS MY REPORT,
ALL RIGHT?

35:12.191 --> 35:13.652
ALL THE PROJECTS
ARE HERE --

35:13.652 --> 35:17.326
OPERATING BUDGETS
VERSUS PROGRESS TO DATE.

35:17.326 --> 35:18.737
BEST TO WORST.

35:18.737 --> 35:20.659
TAKE A LOOK, BUT THE DECISION
IS PRETTY CLEAR TO ME.

35:20.659 --> 35:21.790
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

35:21.790 --> 35:23.242
UH, Y-YOU GOT A SECOND?

35:24.413 --> 35:26.835
NEVER MIND.
I'LL COME BACK.
NO, NO.
ALEX, COME IN.

35:29.248 --> 35:30.299
YOU OKAY?

35:30.299 --> 35:31.710
UH, YEAH. YEAH.

35:31.710 --> 35:33.302
I, UH, JUST WANTED
TO LET YOU KNOW

35:33.302 --> 35:36.635
THAT, UH, MY FELLOWSHIP
IS, UH, ALMOST DONE,

35:36.635 --> 35:38.717
AND, UH...
WELL, I GOT AN OFFER

35:38.717 --> 35:41.600
FROM LeBACKES
PEDIATRIC SURGERY CLINIC,

35:41.600 --> 35:43.312
OLIVER LeBACKES' PRACTICE,

35:43.312 --> 35:44.813
AND, UH...

35:44.813 --> 35:46.975
WELL, I GAVE IT
SOME SERIOUS CONSIDERATION,

35:46.975 --> 35:48.977
AND I'VE DECIDED
TO TAKE IT.

35:50.529 --> 35:52.861
SO, I GUESS
THIS IS MY NOTICE.

35:52.861 --> 35:56.074
♪ I WANT TO KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE THINKING ♪

35:56.074 --> 35:57.776
♪ THERE ARE SOME THINGS...♪

35:57.776 --> 36:00.869
CRISTINA, PLEASE DON'T
DISAPPEAR ON ME AGAIN.

36:00.869 --> 36:01.700
WHERE ARE YOU?

36:01.700 --> 36:03.742
PLEASE, JUST...CALL ME.

36:03.742 --> 36:05.244
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]
HUNT.
WE NEED TO TALK.

36:05.244 --> 36:06.705
IF IT CAN WAIT,
I REALLY --

36:06.705 --> 36:07.836
NO, IT CAN'T.

36:16.295 --> 36:17.386
WELL?

36:17.386 --> 36:19.678
I ALMOST DIDN'T
GO THROUGH WITH IT.

36:19.678 --> 36:21.430
BUT...THEN I DID.

36:21.430 --> 36:23.602
AND I THINK
IT'S GONNA BE GOOD, RIGHT?

36:23.602 --> 36:26.395
[ GASPS ] ARE YOU KIDDING?!
IT'S GONNA BE AWESOME!

36:26.395 --> 36:27.606
BABY!

36:27.606 --> 36:29.518
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:33.572 --> 36:35.153
OH.
COMPARTMENT SYNDROME?

36:35.153 --> 36:37.866
[ GROANS ] YES.
BLOOD WENT EVERYWHERE.

36:37.866 --> 36:39.578
MM. TORRES LOVES
THAT TRICK.

36:39.578 --> 36:41.159
YOU SHOULD
JUST TOSS THOSE.

36:41.159 --> 36:42.411
I KNOW.
YOU'RE RIGHT.

36:42.411 --> 36:44.202
WHY AM I SCRUBBING
THOSE NASTY THINGS,

36:44.202 --> 36:46.875
WHEN NOW YOU CAN AFFORD
TO BUY ME NEW ONES?

36:46.875 --> 36:48.877
[ LAUGHS ]

36:57.135 --> 36:58.507
WHAT HAPPENED?

37:00.178 --> 37:01.800
Meredith: WAIT.
WHERE ARE THE KIDS?

37:01.800 --> 37:03.842
THEY'RE ASLEEP --
TOTALLY FINE.

37:03.842 --> 37:05.223
WHAT'S WRONG?

37:06.475 --> 37:07.726
I CAN'T DO THIS.

37:07.726 --> 37:09.848
THE CHILDREN
BROKE YOUR SISTER.

37:09.848 --> 37:11.189
NO, IT'S NOT THEM.

37:12.691 --> 37:14.903
I DIDN'T COME HERE TO SEE
HOW YOUR PERFECT LIFE WORKED.

37:14.903 --> 37:17.195
I CAME TO SEE
IF I COULD DO IT --

37:17.195 --> 37:19.488
THE WHOLE FREAKING THING,

37:19.488 --> 37:23.121
THE KIDS AND MARRIAGE
AND THE FULL-TIME CAREERS --

37:23.121 --> 37:26.575
BECAUSE I WANT THAT...
WITH JAMES.

37:26.575 --> 37:29.998
[ Voice breaking ]
AND I AM WRECKED AFTER ONE DAY.

37:29.998 --> 37:31.460
[ WHIMPERS ]

37:31.460 --> 37:34.673
IT GOES ON THE LIST OF THINGS
THAT I SUCK AT BECAUSE...

37:36.795 --> 37:39.758
[ Crying ] I CAN'T.
[ SNIFFLES ]

37:39.758 --> 37:40.969
[ WHIMPERS ]

37:40.969 --> 37:42.971
WELL, I KNEW THAT WAS
TOO GOOD TO BE TRUE.

37:42.971 --> 37:44.843
WHY DON'T YOU GO
FIX YOUR SISTER?

37:44.843 --> 37:46.725
I'LL ORDER TAKEOUT.

37:46.725 --> 37:48.727
[ DOOR OPENS, KEYS JINGLE ]

37:55.654 --> 37:56.655
HEY.

37:56.655 --> 37:57.696
HEY.

37:57.696 --> 37:59.658
SO, YOU ARE...

38:02.361 --> 38:04.032
RIGHT.

38:09.458 --> 38:11.209
UH, I'LL SEE YOU
TOMORROW.

38:13.121 --> 38:14.463
APRIL.

38:15.794 --> 38:19.678
I SAID A LOT OF THINGS
THE OTHER NIGHT THAT I REGRET.

38:19.678 --> 38:22.511
AND I'M SORRY
THAT I HURT YOUR FEELINGS.

38:22.511 --> 38:23.552
I'M SORRY, TOO.

38:23.552 --> 38:25.223
GOOD.
SO COME HOME. STAY.

38:25.223 --> 38:27.516
THIS IS A CONVERSATION
WE'RE ALWAYS GONNA HAVE TO HAVE.

38:27.516 --> 38:29.728
IT'S A PART OF WHO WE ARE.
IT'S GONNA TAKE SOME TALKING.

38:29.728 --> 38:31.730
BUT WE GOT MARRIED.
WE LOVE EACH OTHER.

38:31.730 --> 38:33.892
WE MADE VOWS TO PUSH THROUGH
THIS SORT OF THING.

38:33.892 --> 38:35.103
I KNOW.

38:35.103 --> 38:38.196
I LOVE YOU, TOO,
AND WE MADE A COMMITMENT.

38:38.196 --> 38:42.030
AND IF YOU BELIEVE IN GOD,
THEN YOU BELIEVE HE MADE ME --

38:42.030 --> 38:43.782
YOUR HUSBAND...

38:43.782 --> 38:46.204
WHO SHARES YOUR VALUES,
WHICH I DO.

38:46.204 --> 38:47.656
I BELIEVE
WE SHOULDN'T KILL OR STEAL.

38:47.656 --> 38:49.408
I BELIEVE
THAT YOU SHOULD BE TRUTHFUL.

38:49.408 --> 38:50.909
I BELIEVE
THAT YOU SHOULD TREAT OTHERS

38:50.909 --> 38:52.371
THE WAY
YOU WANT TO BE TREATED.

38:52.371 --> 38:53.752
I AGREE.

38:53.752 --> 38:56.665
SO, THEN, WE CAN
PUSH THROUGH THIS PROBLEM.

38:56.665 --> 38:58.507
AT OUR CORE,
WE BELIEVE THE SAME THINGS.

38:58.507 --> 39:00.338
UNTIL I THINK ABOUT
TELLING OUR CHILDREN

39:00.338 --> 39:02.130
HOW UNBELIEVABLY LOVED
THEY ARE

39:02.130 --> 39:04.132
BY THE CREATOR OF THE UNIVERSE,
WHO ALSO MADE THEM,

39:04.132 --> 39:05.844
AND I CAN JUST SEE YOU
STANDING THERE,

39:05.844 --> 39:08.306
JUDGING AND DISMISSIVE,
AND I JUST CAN'T GET PAST IT.

39:08.306 --> 39:09.848
CAN WE PLEASE
JUST TAKE A BREAK

39:09.848 --> 39:11.730
FROM OUR HYPOTHETICAL CHILDREN
FOR --

39:11.730 --> 39:16.144
NO, WE CAN'T, BECAUSE THEY'RE
NOT HYPOTHETICAL ANYMORE.

39:16.144 --> 39:17.566
♪ SAY YOU DON'T KNOW ME ♪

39:17.566 --> 39:19.898
JACKSON, I'M PREGNANT.

39:19.898 --> 39:21.940
Meredith:
SO, WHAT DO YOU DO?

39:21.940 --> 39:24.693
HOW DO YOU DECIDE?

39:24.693 --> 39:27.986
WHEN YOU'RE LEFT IN THE DARK?

39:27.986 --> 39:29.408
♪ THAT KIND OF PLACE ♪

39:29.408 --> 39:30.949
HOW DO YOU MAKE SURE

39:30.949 --> 39:34.042
YOU'RE NOT MAKING THE WORST
MISTAKE OF SOMEONE'S LIFE?

39:34.042 --> 39:35.914
SO, NOW WHAT?

39:35.914 --> 39:40.629
WE JUST...CROSS OUR FINGERS
AND HOPE HE GETS BETTER?

39:40.629 --> 39:42.130
GUESS SO.

39:43.672 --> 39:45.173
GOOD NIGHT, EDWARDS.

39:45.173 --> 39:48.927
♪ EATING UP THE NIGHT ♪

39:48.927 --> 39:52.220
♪ MARCONI PLAYS THE MAMBA ♪

39:52.220 --> 39:53.852
YOU CLOSE YOUR EYES...

39:53.852 --> 39:55.894
♪ LISTEN TO THE RADIO ♪

39:55.894 --> 39:58.687
♪ DON'T YOU REMEMBER? ♪

39:58.687 --> 40:02.400
...YOU BLOCK OUT EVERYONE
AND EVERYTHING AROUND YOU...

40:02.400 --> 40:06.785
♪ WE BUILT THIS CITY ♪

40:06.785 --> 40:07.906
CRISTINA?

40:07.906 --> 40:12.621
♪ ON ROCK 'N' ROLL ♪

40:12.621 --> 40:14.623
[ WATER RUNNING ]

40:14.623 --> 40:16.084
CRISTINA?

40:16.084 --> 40:17.956
CRISTINA?

40:17.956 --> 40:19.417
ARE YOU OKAY?

40:19.417 --> 40:25.634
♪ WE BUILT THIS CITY
ON ROCK 'N' ROLL ♪

40:25.634 --> 40:27.716
CRISTINA,
THEY WERE VERY SICK KIDS.

40:27.716 --> 40:29.137
EVERY ONE OF THEM

40:29.137 --> 40:31.810
WOULD HAVE BEEN LOOKING
AT A DEATH SENTENCE WITHOUT YOU.

40:31.810 --> 40:33.431
THE FACT THAT ANY OF THEM
SURVIVED --

40:33.431 --> 40:34.933
I KNOW THIS, OWEN.

40:34.933 --> 40:39.147
FRANKIE WAS ON BORROWED TIME
FROM THE MOMENT SHE GOT HERE.

40:39.147 --> 40:41.399
YOU MADE THE RIGHT DECISION.
YOU MADE THE RIGHT CALL.

40:41.399 --> 40:44.733
I KNOW I MADE THE RIGHT CALL.
YOU DON'T HAVE TO TELL ME.

40:44.733 --> 40:49.738
IT WAS AN IMPOSSIBLE DECISION,
AND I STAND BY IT.

40:54.162 --> 40:57.335
I DID EVERYTHING...

40:57.335 --> 41:00.999
EXACTLY
AS I WAS SUPPOSED TO.

41:00.999 --> 41:03.381
I DID IT PERFECTLY.

41:04.753 --> 41:07.045
♪ LISTEN TO THE RADIO ♪

41:07.045 --> 41:08.466
SO WHAT IS WRONG?

41:08.466 --> 41:11.720
♪ DON'T YOU REMEMBER ♪

41:13.091 --> 41:14.803
♪ WE BUILT THIS CITY ♪

41:14.803 --> 41:16.725
WHAT'S THE POINT, OWEN?

41:20.979 --> 41:23.191
WHAT'S THE POINT
OF ANYTHING?

41:25.654 --> 41:30.108
♪ WE BUILT THIS CITY
ON ROCK 'N' ROLL ♪

41:30.108 --> 41:32.370
YOU WON.

41:32.370 --> 41:36.575
THE HARPER AVERY --
YOU GOT THE MOST VOTES.

41:36.575 --> 41:39.668
RICHARD JUST TOLD ME.

41:39.668 --> 41:41.419
THE POLITICS
SCREWED YOU.

41:41.419 --> 41:45.423
THE FOUNDATION'S RELATIONSHIP
WITH US -- THEY USED YOU.

41:45.423 --> 41:47.425
[ SCOFFS ]

41:47.425 --> 41:50.839
YOU NEVER STOOD A CHANCE.

41:50.839 --> 41:54.392
♪ WE BUILT THIS CITY
ON ROCK 'N' ROLL ♪

41:54.392 --> 41:58.847
...AND PRAY
THAT THE VOICE INSIDE YOU...

41:58.847 --> 42:01.439
♪ WE BUILT THIS CITY ♪

42:01.439 --> 42:03.772
...IS RIGHT.

42:03.772 --> 42:06.234
♪ BUILT THIS CITY ♪

42:06.234 --> 42:07.696
BECAUSE ONCE YOU'VE DECIDED...

42:07.696 --> 42:11.740
♪ WE BUILT THIS CITY
ON ROCK 'N' ROLL ♪

42:11.740 --> 42:13.702
♪ BUILT THIS CITY ♪

42:13.702 --> 42:15.864
...YOU CAN'T EVER GO BACK.

42:15.864 --> 42:23.121
♪ WE BUILT THIS CITY
ON ROCK 'N' ROLL ♪
